1
00:00:10,301 --> 00:00:13,138
THE LOVE LAB

2
00:00:13,722 --> 00:00:16,599
<i>Two kinds of love experiments</i>
<i>will be conducted today.</i>

3
00:00:17,976 --> 00:00:19,185
<i>The first one is</i>

4
00:00:20,353 --> 00:00:21,563
<i>Drunk Blind Date.</i>

5
00:00:22,647 --> 00:00:23,523
<i>And…</i>

6
00:00:23,606 --> 00:00:25,525
<i>You've been invited</i>
<i>to the King of Hearts game.</i>

7
00:00:25,608 --> 00:00:27,402
-I'm scared.
-What's that?

8
00:00:27,485 --> 00:00:28,945
It'll give me a dopamine rush.

9
00:00:29,029 --> 00:00:30,572
Want to go on a date with me tomorrow?

10
00:00:30,655 --> 00:00:33,199
<i>It's entirely up to the king.</i>

11
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:34,826
I'll let you go on a date
if I become king.

12
00:00:34,909 --> 00:00:36,411
I suddenly want to overturn it.

13
00:00:36,494 --> 00:00:38,079
<i>It's the King of Hearts game.</i>

14
00:00:38,163 --> 00:00:41,041
KING OF HEARTS GAME

15
00:00:41,124 --> 00:00:43,376
<i>The third Love Lab experiment is</i>

16
00:00:44,335 --> 00:00:46,254
<i>Drunk Blind Date.</i>

17
00:00:46,337 --> 00:00:49,716
<i>What if someone went on a blind date…</i>

18
00:00:49,799 --> 00:00:52,218
-Shall we clink our glasses?
<i>-…with a blood alcohol level of 0.08%?</i>

19
00:00:52,886 --> 00:00:57,390
<i>Melting away the looks, backgrounds,</i>
<i>and circumstances in alcohol,</i>

20
00:00:57,474 --> 00:01:01,853
<i>the man and woman must face each other</i>
<i>only in their drunk state.</i>

21
00:01:02,812 --> 00:01:05,648
<i>Will the alcohol help with their romance</i>

22
00:01:05,732 --> 00:01:08,193
<i>or will it become a hindrance?</i>

23
00:01:08,276 --> 00:01:10,862
DRUNK BLIND DATE

24
00:01:10,945 --> 00:01:12,072
Of course, it'll help.

25
00:01:12,155 --> 00:01:14,407
If I enjoyed drinking,
I wouldn't be single.

26
00:01:16,659 --> 00:01:18,036
This sounds so interesting though.

27
00:01:18,119 --> 00:01:19,996
How drunk are you if it's 0.08%?

28
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:23,374
-You wouldn't really call that "drunk."
-Just a bit buzzed?

29
00:01:23,458 --> 00:01:24,375
Not even buzzed.

30
00:01:24,459 --> 00:01:26,169
Your driver's license can get canceled.

31
00:01:27,629 --> 00:01:29,255
Then, they're completely drunk.

32
00:01:29,339 --> 00:01:31,341
-Really?
-On a date while intoxicated?

33
00:01:34,135 --> 00:01:35,970
SUBJECT 1
KANG JUNG-WOO

34
00:01:36,054 --> 00:01:38,765
You prefer someone
who has cat-like features?

35
00:01:38,848 --> 00:01:39,682
Yes.

36
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:42,685
I like someone who's tall
and has long hair.

37
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:43,895
And someone who is honest.

38
00:01:44,395 --> 00:01:45,897
SUBJECT 2
HA SEUNG-AH

39
00:01:45,980 --> 00:01:47,023
Weren't you surprised?

40
00:01:47,106 --> 00:01:49,776
Yeah, I really thought it was a scam.

41
00:01:49,859 --> 00:01:51,820
-Really?
-It's happened before.

42
00:01:51,903 --> 00:01:54,197
-You do have to be careful.
-For real.

43
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:56,116
Your MBTI is ISTJ.

44
00:01:56,199 --> 00:01:57,450
Yes, that's right.

45
00:01:57,992 --> 00:01:59,160
Dating must be tough for you.

46
00:02:00,912 --> 00:02:05,792
I'm attracted to someone who's tall,
has a good physique,

47
00:02:05,875 --> 00:02:08,753
and a not overly-pretty face.

48
00:02:08,837 --> 00:02:12,090
You like someone like Ahn Bo-hyun,
so a boy-next-door type?

49
00:02:12,173 --> 00:02:14,259
Yes, I like that.

50
00:02:14,342 --> 00:02:18,972
Yes, I think alcohol would help
with breaking the ice at first.

51
00:02:19,055 --> 00:02:22,142
It would also help
when having deep conversations.

52
00:02:22,225 --> 00:02:24,686
THE EXPERIMENT TOPIC
HAS BEEN INFORMED TO SUBJECT 1

53
00:02:25,270 --> 00:02:27,272
You start the date off drunk.

54
00:02:28,189 --> 00:02:29,190
Oh.

55
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:31,985
You'll drink with us
before you go on the date.

56
00:02:32,068 --> 00:02:33,319
I like that.

57
00:02:33,403 --> 00:02:36,698
I think I can meet her
in a more relaxed state.

58
00:02:36,781 --> 00:02:39,617
SUBJECT 2 HAS BEEN
OFFERED THE DRUNK BLIND DATE TOO

59
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:41,828
That sounds nice.

60
00:02:44,205 --> 00:02:46,291
Do you think alcohol helps
when it comes to romance?

61
00:02:46,374 --> 00:02:48,126
Yes, I think it helps.

62
00:02:48,209 --> 00:02:49,836
It's so awkward when you meet at first.

63
00:02:49,919 --> 00:02:52,297
I think it'd be better
to go on a blind date

64
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:54,424
after having a few drinks.

65
00:02:54,507 --> 00:02:55,633
It sounds fun.

66
00:02:55,717 --> 00:02:58,011
THE FIRST DATE

67
00:02:58,094 --> 00:02:59,012
Cheers.

68
00:02:59,095 --> 00:03:00,096
Thank you.

69
00:03:00,179 --> 00:03:04,434
SUBJECTS 1 AND 2 ARE GETTING DRUNK
BEFORE THE BLIND DATE

70
00:03:05,894 --> 00:03:07,145
So that's how they do it.

71
00:03:07,228 --> 00:03:09,898
-They go for a drink with the crew first.
-Yeah.

72
00:03:09,981 --> 00:03:11,357
Then, go on the blind date drunk.

73
00:03:11,441 --> 00:03:12,483
Wow.

74
00:03:12,567 --> 00:03:16,362
Wait, so how do you know
if they are drunk?

75
00:03:16,446 --> 00:03:20,325
You need to reach a certain
blood alcohol level before you can start.

76
00:03:20,408 --> 00:03:22,493
Our goal is 0.08%.

77
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:24,662
You can only start
when you reach that level.

78
00:03:24,746 --> 00:03:26,122
Really?

79
00:03:26,205 --> 00:03:27,832
I should drink a lot then.

80
00:03:27,916 --> 00:03:30,335
We'll let you start
as soon as you get drunk.

81
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:34,088
THEY MUST GET DRUNK
TO GO ON THE BLIND DATE

82
00:03:37,050 --> 00:03:38,009
Did I make it?

83
00:03:38,801 --> 00:03:39,886
I got 0.03%.

84
00:03:39,969 --> 00:03:42,138
SHE STILL HAS A LONG WAY TO GO

85
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:44,515
-He got it.
-Did he?

86
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,101
LACKING 0.01

87
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:48,895
-What is it?
-0.07.

88
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:52,190
JUNG-WOO CAN'T WAIT
TO GO ON THE BLIND DATE

89
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:57,403
QUALIFIED TO GO ON THE BLIND DATE

90
00:03:57,987 --> 00:03:59,822
-Do I go now? Okay.
-Yes.

91
00:04:00,531 --> 00:04:03,493
I got 0.04%. It went up 0.01.

92
00:04:03,576 --> 00:04:06,454
JEONG BAEK-SUN SUNDAE RESTAURANT IN PANGYO

93
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:20,593
HE DISCOVERS SOMETHING

94
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:22,971
DRUNK BLIND DATE GUIDE
ASK ANY QUESTIONS EXCEPT FOR JOB AND AGE

95
00:04:23,054 --> 00:04:24,681
THE DATE BEGINS
AS SOON AS YOU CLINK GLASSES

96
00:04:24,764 --> 00:04:28,893
Except for job and age.

97
00:04:29,477 --> 00:04:31,604
Except for job and age.

98
00:04:31,688 --> 00:04:33,273
MEANWHILE, SEUNG-AH IS…

99
00:04:33,356 --> 00:04:35,733
They go like, "I'm sleepy."

100
00:04:35,817 --> 00:04:38,987
You should just plainly say
that you're sleepy instead.

101
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:42,073
But they go, "I'm sleepy."

102
00:04:47,704 --> 00:04:49,622
-What is it?
-It says I can go now.

103
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:53,751
SHE CAN FINALLY GO ON HER BLIND DATE

104
00:04:53,835 --> 00:04:55,253
I'm nervous.

105
00:04:55,336 --> 00:04:57,922
I'm really getting nervous.

106
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:33,666
Hello.

107
00:05:39,088 --> 00:05:40,298
Hello.

108
00:05:44,719 --> 00:05:47,221
Oh, my. They're into each other already.

109
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:49,766
Come on. I have no doubt
that they'll end up together.

110
00:05:49,849 --> 00:05:51,392
-They're done.
-It already worked out.

111
00:05:51,476 --> 00:05:53,644
They look so good together.
I can picture them dating.

112
00:05:53,728 --> 00:05:55,354
Go ahead and stuff your face.

113
00:05:55,438 --> 00:05:56,522
Nice to meet you.

114
00:05:57,231 --> 00:05:58,191
Nice to meet you.

115
00:06:06,074 --> 00:06:07,200
May I ask your name?

116
00:06:07,283 --> 00:06:08,367
I'm Kang Jung-woo.

117
00:06:08,451 --> 00:06:09,577
-Kang Jung-woo?
-Yes.

118
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:10,495
And you?

119
00:06:10,578 --> 00:06:12,038
I'm Ha Seung-ah.

120
00:06:12,121 --> 00:06:13,081
-Ha Seung-ah?
-Yes.

121
00:06:13,164 --> 00:06:14,624
Okay. Ha Seung-ah.

122
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:17,251
Nice to meet you.

123
00:06:17,335 --> 00:06:19,295
FIRST DRUNK BLIND DATE

124
00:06:19,378 --> 00:06:21,756
2 HOURS LATER,
WE CONDUCTED AN INTERVIEW

125
00:06:23,049 --> 00:06:24,258
How are you doing right now?

126
00:06:25,343 --> 00:06:27,095
I'm too drunk.

127
00:06:27,178 --> 00:06:29,180
ALL INTERVIEWS WERE CONDUCTED WHILE DRUNK

128
00:06:29,263 --> 00:06:32,016
Did you see Seung-ah's face
when she walked in?

129
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:33,184
-Yes.
-What did you think?

130
00:06:34,602 --> 00:06:38,106
I thought she was pretty
because she had the cat-like look I like.

131
00:06:38,189 --> 00:06:39,190
CHUCKLE

132
00:06:39,273 --> 00:06:41,317
You thought she was pretty
as soon as you saw her?

133
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,485
Yes.

134
00:06:43,194 --> 00:06:44,237
WOBBLE

135
00:06:45,154 --> 00:06:46,239
Should I have you sit down?

136
00:06:46,322 --> 00:06:48,449
WE HAD HIM SIT DOWN

137
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:50,201
The doggy…

138
00:06:50,284 --> 00:06:51,828
ANOTHER DRUNK PERSON

139
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:53,079
My first impression?

140
00:06:53,913 --> 00:06:58,376
He came across
as a really hardworking young man.

141
00:06:59,585 --> 00:07:00,419
In a good way.

142
00:07:00,503 --> 00:07:02,630
He looked handsome.

143
00:07:02,713 --> 00:07:04,298
-Shall we clink our glasses?
-Yes.

144
00:07:04,382 --> 00:07:05,466
Nice to meet you.

145
00:07:09,637 --> 00:07:11,264
I prepared hangover supplements.

146
00:07:11,347 --> 00:07:12,390
-Really?
-Yes.

147
00:07:12,473 --> 00:07:13,891
Are you a mint chocolate lover?

148
00:07:13,975 --> 00:07:16,102
I have mint chocolate
and regular chocolate.

149
00:07:16,185 --> 00:07:17,437
I'll take regular chocolate.

150
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:18,479
-Chocolate?
-Yes.

151
00:07:18,563 --> 00:07:19,981
I do like mint chocolate,

152
00:07:20,606 --> 00:07:22,316
but I'm craving something sweet right now.

153
00:07:27,238 --> 00:07:28,072
Isn't it good?

154
00:07:28,781 --> 00:07:29,657
Very chocolatey.

155
00:07:31,617 --> 00:07:33,244
Do you like <i>sundae gukbap?</i>

156
00:07:33,327 --> 00:07:37,957
Yes, I do. It's surprisingly fancy
for a <i>sundae gukbap</i> place.

157
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:39,917
-Right?
-I didn't know they served this here.

158
00:07:46,132 --> 00:07:46,966
It's tasty.

159
00:07:47,049 --> 00:07:48,885
-Is the seasoning okay?
-Yes, it's very good.

160
00:07:48,968 --> 00:07:50,094
Shall we clink our glasses?

161
00:07:54,724 --> 00:07:56,642
If you don't mind me asking,
where are you from?

162
00:07:57,727 --> 00:07:59,228
Where do you think I'm from?

163
00:07:59,729 --> 00:08:01,606
You have a very familiar intonation.

164
00:08:01,689 --> 00:08:03,191
-You aren't from Seoul, are you?
-No.

165
00:08:03,274 --> 00:08:05,026
-I'm from Gyeongsang-do.
-Really?

166
00:08:05,109 --> 00:08:06,861
You're from Gyeongsang-do too.

167
00:08:06,944 --> 00:08:09,030
-Where in Gyeongsang-do are you from?
-I'm from Daegu.

168
00:08:09,113 --> 00:08:10,323
-Daegu?
-Yes.

169
00:08:10,406 --> 00:08:12,033
-Are you from Daegu?
-I'm from Gimhae.

170
00:08:12,116 --> 00:08:13,993
-You know Gimhae, right?
-Gimhae? Of course.

171
00:08:14,076 --> 00:08:16,579
-How long have you been in Seoul?
-Me?

172
00:08:16,662 --> 00:08:17,747
I've been here a long time.

173
00:08:17,830 --> 00:08:19,040
Five or six years?

174
00:08:19,123 --> 00:08:20,208
You can't tell, right?

175
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:24,962
Because we're from the same area…

176
00:08:25,046 --> 00:08:26,422
You could tell immediately.

177
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:28,925
I wouldn't be able to tell
if we weren't from the same area.

178
00:08:29,008 --> 00:08:30,468
-But because we are…
-Right?

179
00:08:30,551 --> 00:08:32,720
-You can't tell if you aren't.
-Right.

180
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,601
Do you like <i>gukbap?</i>

181
00:08:39,101 --> 00:08:40,394
It must be hot.

182
00:08:42,813 --> 00:08:44,148
<i>Gukbap </i>is

183
00:08:44,232 --> 00:08:45,149
my soul food.

184
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:46,484
-Really?
-Yes.

185
00:08:46,567 --> 00:08:47,485
I see.

186
00:08:47,568 --> 00:08:49,278
-If you're from Gyeongsang-do…
-Yes?

187
00:08:49,362 --> 00:08:50,696
-Pork <i>gukbap</i>?
-Pork <i>gukbap</i>.

188
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:52,156
-Right?
-I love pork <i>gukbap</i>.

189
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,200
I really love pork <i>gukbap</i>.

190
00:08:54,283 --> 00:08:55,201
-Really?
-Yes.

191
00:08:55,284 --> 00:08:57,870
I don't like it that much.

192
00:08:58,371 --> 00:09:00,122
How did you get rid of your dialect?

193
00:09:02,250 --> 00:09:03,709
IT'S TOO HOT AGAIN

194
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:08,381
-Cool it off first.
-I should turn the burner off.

195
00:09:09,507 --> 00:09:11,217
What kind of food do you like?

196
00:09:11,300 --> 00:09:13,803
Do you like old-school restaurants?

197
00:09:13,886 --> 00:09:14,929
-I do.
-Really?

198
00:09:15,012 --> 00:09:16,931
-Yeah.
-I love places like that.

199
00:09:17,014 --> 00:09:19,767
Those old and shabby…

200
00:09:21,185 --> 00:09:22,603
You should slow down.

201
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:25,147
THAT WOULD PROBABLY BE BEST

202
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:28,818
<i>He enjoyed the </i>gukbap
<i>way more than I expected.</i>

203
00:09:28,901 --> 00:09:29,735
It was hot,

204
00:09:30,444 --> 00:09:32,321
but he ate it going like this.

205
00:09:33,739 --> 00:09:36,450
He went like this but kept eating it.

206
00:09:38,369 --> 00:09:40,162
It's hot.

207
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:42,873
I think you burnt your throat.

208
00:09:42,957 --> 00:09:44,292
It won't cool down.

209
00:09:44,875 --> 00:09:45,960
Did you really turn it off?

210
00:09:46,043 --> 00:09:47,670
-I did.
-You should turn it off.

211
00:09:47,753 --> 00:09:48,588
It's so hot.

212
00:09:49,547 --> 00:09:51,090
You're such a prince.

213
00:09:51,173 --> 00:09:52,675
Sorry. What did you say you like?

214
00:09:52,758 --> 00:09:53,843
Old-school, dirty places.

215
00:09:53,926 --> 00:09:55,428
Old-school, dirty places?

216
00:09:55,511 --> 00:09:56,679
Kind of…

217
00:09:57,430 --> 00:10:00,349
You know those places
that are shabby and dirty.

218
00:10:00,433 --> 00:10:03,060
You know what kind of vibe
I'm talking about, right?

219
00:10:03,144 --> 00:10:04,604
What's your MBTI?

220
00:10:04,687 --> 00:10:06,397
-Can I guess?
-Okay.

221
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,857
INTP.

222
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:09,275
You got it right except for one.

223
00:10:09,358 --> 00:10:10,526
-Really?
-Yes.

224
00:10:10,610 --> 00:10:11,652
You must be INTJ.

225
00:10:11,736 --> 00:10:13,404
You got the first part wrong.

226
00:10:13,487 --> 00:10:14,655
ENTP?

227
00:10:14,739 --> 00:10:15,573
That's right.

228
00:10:15,656 --> 00:10:17,366
-Really?
-Yes.

229
00:10:17,450 --> 00:10:20,244
<i>Honestly, when I found out he was ENTP,</i>

230
00:10:20,328 --> 00:10:22,955
I became a little hesitant.

231
00:10:23,039 --> 00:10:27,710
I think ENTPs tend to be

232
00:10:27,793 --> 00:10:29,503
a little bit emotional.

233
00:10:29,587 --> 00:10:31,339
I'm sure some aren't though.

234
00:10:31,422 --> 00:10:35,176
So I was a little taken aback by that.

235
00:10:35,259 --> 00:10:37,303
-I'll try to guess yours too.
-Go ahead.

236
00:10:39,347 --> 00:10:40,473
ISTP.

237
00:10:41,557 --> 00:10:42,767
Why did you think that?

238
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:45,478
I went with "I" because you seem quiet,

239
00:10:45,561 --> 00:10:47,563
and a lot of people
from Gyeongsang-do are Ts.

240
00:10:48,856 --> 00:10:50,191
That's how I got IST.

241
00:10:50,274 --> 00:10:51,609
I'm ISTJ.

242
00:10:51,692 --> 00:10:55,029
-ISTJ?
-But I'm almost 50-50 between J and P.

243
00:10:57,531 --> 00:10:59,325
Two Ts met. That's nice.

244
00:10:59,408 --> 00:11:00,910
Want to know something awesome?

245
00:11:00,993 --> 00:11:02,328
-Yeah?
-They only share the T.

246
00:11:02,411 --> 00:11:04,580
You're right. Does this have
some kind of formula?

247
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:05,539
Not really.

248
00:11:07,124 --> 00:11:08,459
I'm ISTJ.

249
00:11:08,542 --> 00:11:11,921
-ISTJ?
-But I'm almost 50-50 between J and P.

250
00:11:14,382 --> 00:11:19,970
It was the first time in my life
meeting a person who is ISTP.

251
00:11:20,054 --> 00:11:24,975
The usual steps for turning a blind date

252
00:11:25,059 --> 00:11:27,937
into something more

253
00:11:28,020 --> 00:11:29,772
didn't work on that person.

254
00:11:29,855 --> 00:11:30,898
It didn't work.

255
00:11:30,981 --> 00:11:34,193
Yeah, ISTPs are the hardest
at starting to date.

256
00:11:34,276 --> 00:11:36,570
When you like someone,
you contact regularly

257
00:11:36,654 --> 00:11:38,447
and make plans for next time.

258
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:39,740
Those are normal, right?

259
00:11:39,824 --> 00:11:41,158
But I couldn't get a hold of her.

260
00:11:41,242 --> 00:11:43,744
She left my messages unread
for two days, twice.

261
00:11:43,828 --> 00:11:46,455
Then, she canceled our next plans.

262
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:48,999
When she said, "See you next time,"

263
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,793
I said, "Okay, take care."

264
00:11:50,876 --> 00:11:53,379
It was my way of saying goodbye,

265
00:11:53,462 --> 00:11:56,882
but she replied and said,
"Why did you tell me to 'take care'?"

266
00:11:56,966 --> 00:12:01,011
I realized that I could never
really understand her,

267
00:12:01,095 --> 00:12:02,930
so I called it quits.

268
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:05,808
-Seung-ah is ISTJ.
-Yes.

269
00:12:05,891 --> 00:12:07,518
What do you think she'll be like?

270
00:12:07,601 --> 00:12:10,646
The important thing is that she is IST.

271
00:12:10,729 --> 00:12:13,274
I thought that I'd have to
make a real effort.

272
00:12:13,357 --> 00:12:16,152
I guess I could use what I studied.

273
00:12:16,235 --> 00:12:18,195
After learning more about people like her,

274
00:12:18,279 --> 00:12:22,324
I realized they might express themselves
differently than I thought.

275
00:12:22,408 --> 00:12:25,119
At first, because we think so differently,

276
00:12:25,202 --> 00:12:27,413
I thought she wasn't interested in me.

277
00:12:27,496 --> 00:12:29,081
But after learning more about them,

278
00:12:29,165 --> 00:12:33,794
I realized this might just be
how ISTs express their feelings.

279
00:12:33,878 --> 00:12:38,382
They're hard to figure out,
confusing, and ambiguous.

280
00:12:38,466 --> 00:12:39,758
How did you study about them?

281
00:12:40,384 --> 00:12:41,385
On YouTube.

282
00:12:44,472 --> 00:12:48,934
Did you know that contents related to ISTs
get the most views on YouTube?

283
00:12:50,644 --> 00:12:51,562
ISTP?

284
00:12:51,645 --> 00:12:53,147
-You see? YouTube…
-He watched a lot.

285
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:55,274
-He watched a lot.
-Yeah, he did.

286
00:12:56,442 --> 00:12:57,568
Yes, one person.

287
00:12:57,651 --> 00:13:00,362
ONLY JUNG-WOO RECEIVED A TEXT MESSAGE

288
00:13:00,446 --> 00:13:03,157
ARE YOU INTERESTED
IN THE PERSON IN FRONT OF YOU?

289
00:13:03,240 --> 00:13:06,952
IF YOU ARE, POUR A DRINK IN HER GLASS
BASED ON HOW MUCH YOU LIKE HER

290
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:12,291
Let me pour you a drink.

291
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:16,962
ENTP.

292
00:13:17,588 --> 00:13:19,298
What is your take on that?

293
00:13:19,381 --> 00:13:20,424
HE POURED ONE FOR HIMSELF?

294
00:13:20,508 --> 00:13:21,592
-ENTP?
-Yes.

295
00:13:21,675 --> 00:13:23,260
I think I read it as

296
00:13:23,761 --> 00:13:26,138
"If you don't like her,
pour a glass for yourself.

297
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:29,391
If you like her, pour a glass for her."

298
00:13:29,475 --> 00:13:33,354
We told you to pour her a glass
based on how much you like her.

299
00:13:33,437 --> 00:13:36,440
I didn't catch the latter part
because I was drunk.

300
00:13:36,524 --> 00:13:38,317
How much would you pour
if you did it again?

301
00:13:39,777 --> 00:13:43,239
I'd fill the soju glass to 90%.

302
00:13:45,282 --> 00:13:47,535
We only just met.

303
00:13:49,119 --> 00:13:52,289
I guess this may be the power of alcohol.

304
00:13:53,707 --> 00:13:55,376
May I ask what your ideal type is?

305
00:13:55,459 --> 00:13:56,877
-My ideal type?
-Yes.

306
00:13:56,961 --> 00:14:00,756
I like someone who isn't overly pretty

307
00:14:00,839 --> 00:14:03,676
and I'd like him to be tall.

308
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:07,513
I think it'd be nice
if he's 10 cm taller than me.

309
00:14:07,596 --> 00:14:08,556
Are you 168 cm?

310
00:14:08,639 --> 00:14:10,182
-Wow.
-Am I right?

311
00:14:10,266 --> 00:14:11,141
I'm 169 cm.

312
00:14:11,225 --> 00:14:12,351
Oh.

313
00:14:12,434 --> 00:14:15,771
If you add 10 cm to 169…

314
00:14:15,854 --> 00:14:16,689
Okay.

315
00:14:16,772 --> 00:14:18,732
-How tall are you?
-I'm right at 180 cm.

316
00:14:18,816 --> 00:14:20,568
-Really?
-Yes, I'm 180 cm on the dot.

317
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:22,611
I pass.

318
00:14:24,196 --> 00:14:25,281
What's your ideal type?

319
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:28,325
I like someone
who's bright and responsive.

320
00:14:29,785 --> 00:14:30,619
Yeah.

321
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:33,539
What about appearance-wise?

322
00:14:33,622 --> 00:14:36,750
I like someone who's tall
and has long hair.

323
00:14:38,335 --> 00:14:39,169
Yeah.

324
00:14:40,045 --> 00:14:41,589
That sounds like me.

325
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:45,634
"That sounds like me."

326
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:46,635
It's you.

327
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:48,387
-That's right.
-That's right.

328
00:14:48,971 --> 00:14:50,556
That's right.

329
00:14:51,223 --> 00:14:52,892
-Yes.
-I'm just kidding.

330
00:14:52,975 --> 00:14:54,935
No, you're really right.

331
00:14:55,019 --> 00:14:57,313
Who's your favorite celebrity?

332
00:14:57,396 --> 00:14:58,772
Sana?

333
00:14:58,856 --> 00:15:00,441
She has cat-like features, right?

334
00:15:00,524 --> 00:15:02,359
Yeah, she does.

335
00:15:02,443 --> 00:15:04,236
You have cat-like features too.

336
00:15:04,320 --> 00:15:05,946
-I do?
-Yes.

337
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:07,865
-Really?
-Yes.

338
00:15:07,948 --> 00:15:11,410
I never thought I had cat-like features,

339
00:15:11,493 --> 00:15:13,704
but he said I had them.

340
00:15:15,331 --> 00:15:16,206
Well…

341
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:18,542
I guess I'm his ideal type?

342
00:15:21,337 --> 00:15:23,339
What have people said about your looks?

343
00:15:23,422 --> 00:15:25,007
Me? That I have a Jindo dog face.

344
00:15:25,090 --> 00:15:26,884
-A dog?
-Yes.

345
00:15:26,967 --> 00:15:31,013
People say I look like a Jindo dog
or white rice.

346
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:32,640
I've heard that often.

347
00:15:34,850 --> 00:15:35,809
-This white rice?
-Yes.

348
00:15:35,893 --> 00:15:38,479
They say I look like white rice.

349
00:15:40,105 --> 00:15:42,232
-Who told you that?
-A friend.

350
00:15:43,275 --> 00:15:45,569
-You have cat-like features. Definitely.
-Really?

351
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:52,201
She has cat-like features
with a cold vibe.

352
00:15:52,284 --> 00:15:53,661
That was very attractive.

353
00:15:53,744 --> 00:15:55,621
<i>I could even have a crush on her.</i>

354
00:15:55,704 --> 00:15:56,622
<i>That's how I felt.</i>

355
00:15:56,705 --> 00:15:59,708
Women who are cold but pretty
make me nervous.

356
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:01,460
What is your all-time favorite movie?

357
00:16:01,543 --> 00:16:03,170
-All-time favorite movie?
-Yes.

358
00:16:03,253 --> 00:16:07,216
There was one that I saw recently.
I can't remember it all of a sudden.

359
00:16:07,299 --> 00:16:08,509
What's it about?

360
00:16:08,592 --> 00:16:10,135
It's a foreign film,

361
00:16:10,219 --> 00:16:14,515
and it's about understanding
and love within a family.

362
00:16:14,598 --> 00:16:17,643
Does it involve traveling through space?

363
00:16:17,726 --> 00:16:21,480
No, it doesn't go into space, but…

364
00:16:21,563 --> 00:16:23,774
<i>Everything Everywhere All at Once?</i>

365
00:16:23,857 --> 00:16:25,651
-Did I get it right?
-Yes, you did.

366
00:16:25,734 --> 00:16:27,695
-Hey.
-Wow.

367
00:16:27,778 --> 00:16:28,612
That's my…

368
00:16:28,696 --> 00:16:32,282
-That's my all-time favorite movie.
-For real?

369
00:16:32,366 --> 00:16:33,367
No way.

370
00:16:33,450 --> 00:16:34,910
-Seriously. Yes.
-Really?

371
00:16:35,577 --> 00:16:37,997
-It's <i>Everything Everywhere All at Once</i>?
-Yes, that's it.

372
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:39,206
That's crazy.

373
00:16:39,289 --> 00:16:41,458
Whenever I think of
my all-time favorite movie,

374
00:16:41,542 --> 00:16:43,127
I think of that one.

375
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:45,045
The fact that she said that too…

376
00:16:46,630 --> 00:16:47,840
It was very surprising.

377
00:16:47,923 --> 00:16:49,591
Not everyone likes that movie.

378
00:16:49,675 --> 00:16:51,927
So when he said it was
his all-time favorite movie,

379
00:16:52,011 --> 00:16:53,595
I liked that about him.

380
00:16:53,679 --> 00:16:56,056
-I really like it.
-That really gave me goose bumps.

381
00:16:56,140 --> 00:16:58,308
Wow, we need to drink to that.

382
00:16:58,934 --> 00:17:00,310
That's so amazing.

383
00:17:06,316 --> 00:17:07,901
I've never seen that movie.

384
00:17:07,985 --> 00:17:09,903
Having the same
all-time favorite movie is huge.

385
00:17:09,987 --> 00:17:11,321
-Yeah.
-It's really appealing.

386
00:17:11,405 --> 00:17:13,449
When you realize

387
00:17:13,532 --> 00:17:16,952
you have similar interests
and you have good banter while drinking,

388
00:17:17,036 --> 00:17:19,580
that would make you
fall for them even more.

389
00:17:19,663 --> 00:17:22,082
You said you never
heard of that movie, right?

390
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:23,917
-Never.
-They'll read into that.

391
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:26,628
"Hey, my friends haven't
even watched this movie."

392
00:17:26,712 --> 00:17:29,173
If they said a movie like <i>Avengers</i>,
it wouldn't matter at all.

393
00:17:32,009 --> 00:17:33,469
How drunk are you?

394
00:17:34,094 --> 00:17:35,304
Right now?

395
00:17:35,387 --> 00:17:36,305
About 70%?

396
00:17:36,388 --> 00:17:38,432
Is there anything
you want to know about me?

397
00:17:43,270 --> 00:17:44,396
When was your last relationship?

398
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:45,939
-My last relationship?
-Yes.

399
00:17:46,523 --> 00:17:49,318
It's been four years.
I'm on my fifth year now.

400
00:17:50,402 --> 00:17:51,653
Since my last relationship.

401
00:17:53,322 --> 00:17:55,365
Your last relationship was five years ago?

402
00:17:55,449 --> 00:17:56,283
Yes.

403
00:17:57,034 --> 00:17:59,828
-I haven't dated anyone for a long time.
-Yeah.

404
00:18:01,538 --> 00:18:03,290
-That's a really long time.
-Yes.

405
00:18:06,043 --> 00:18:06,960
What?

406
00:18:07,044 --> 00:18:08,670
Seung-ah's been single for a long time.

407
00:18:08,754 --> 00:18:10,047
I'd like that about her.

408
00:18:10,130 --> 00:18:11,465
If she chose me,

409
00:18:11,548 --> 00:18:14,134
it wouldn't be because she's just
looking for anybody to date.

410
00:18:14,218 --> 00:18:16,220
It'd be because she really likes me.

411
00:18:16,303 --> 00:18:17,429
Yeah, I suppose so.

412
00:18:17,513 --> 00:18:19,473
And the fact that it's been that long

413
00:18:19,556 --> 00:18:22,142
means she didn't break up
with someone to be on a dating show.

414
00:18:23,644 --> 00:18:27,022
I tend to have long gaps
between relationships.

415
00:18:27,606 --> 00:18:32,444
And I'm satisfied with
living my life as a single person.

416
00:18:32,528 --> 00:18:35,405
Since I haven't dated for so long,

417
00:18:35,489 --> 00:18:37,908
it's gotten harder for me to date.

418
00:18:37,991 --> 00:18:38,951
Five years…

419
00:18:39,576 --> 00:18:41,286
-It's been four or five years?
-Yeah.

420
00:18:41,912 --> 00:18:43,247
<i>Honestly, I was surprised.</i>

421
00:18:43,330 --> 00:18:46,458
Seung-ah clearly knows what she wants.

422
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:48,710
Since she seems to have
very clear standards,

423
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:53,757
I was a bit worried
that I might not meet those standards.

424
00:18:53,841 --> 00:18:54,800
Excuse me.

425
00:18:55,634 --> 00:18:56,802
Can we have another bottle?

426
00:18:57,302 --> 00:18:59,847
-When was your last relationship?
-It's been about six months.

427
00:19:00,430 --> 00:19:01,390
That's pretty recent.

428
00:19:02,266 --> 00:19:03,767
Compared to five years, it is.

429
00:19:06,061 --> 00:19:08,272
-May I ask you something?
-What is it?

430
00:19:08,355 --> 00:19:10,732
-Could you pick the top two things…
-Okay.

431
00:19:10,816 --> 00:19:12,693
…that make you feel loved the most?

432
00:19:12,776 --> 00:19:14,611
I'll give you five examples.

433
00:19:14,695 --> 00:19:15,988
Go ahead.

434
00:19:16,071 --> 00:19:17,322
Encouraging words.

435
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:19,950
"You're a really great girlfriend."

436
00:19:20,033 --> 00:19:22,744
A small gift. "This made me think of you."

437
00:19:23,495 --> 00:19:25,289
Time spent together.

438
00:19:25,372 --> 00:19:28,750
Someone who likes to focus
on their time together.

439
00:19:28,834 --> 00:19:33,213
And gifts. But these gifts
aren't expensive ones.

440
00:19:34,089 --> 00:19:35,382
Did I already mention that?

441
00:19:35,465 --> 00:19:36,383
I didn't, did I?

442
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:39,469
-"This made me think of you."
-Okay.

443
00:19:41,430 --> 00:19:43,974
I'm starting to smell the alcohol
through the monitor.

444
00:19:44,057 --> 00:19:47,811
Something that the other person
does for you.

445
00:19:48,395 --> 00:19:51,773
The other person does something for you
that you don't like to do.

446
00:19:51,857 --> 00:19:56,111
Of those five things,
pick the top two things…

447
00:19:56,195 --> 00:19:58,739
-Top two?
-…that make you feel loved.

448
00:19:58,822 --> 00:19:59,781
Number four.

449
00:20:00,657 --> 00:20:01,491
What was it again?

450
00:20:03,535 --> 00:20:06,038
Number four? What was it?

451
00:20:06,121 --> 00:20:07,623
NUMBER 4 WAS GIFTS

452
00:20:07,706 --> 00:20:12,336
Words, action,
gifts, service, and physical touch.

453
00:20:12,419 --> 00:20:14,504
TIME DISAPPEARS, PHYSICAL TOUCH APPEARS

454
00:20:15,088 --> 00:20:16,465
Number four.

455
00:20:16,548 --> 00:20:18,467
-Action?
-Yes, action.

456
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:19,468
Being willing

457
00:20:19,968 --> 00:20:21,386
-to do something for you.
-Yes.

458
00:20:21,470 --> 00:20:25,224
If you show it through actions
rather than just words…

459
00:20:25,307 --> 00:20:26,934
-What's the second one?
-The second one?

460
00:20:27,017 --> 00:20:28,727
What was number one?

461
00:20:28,810 --> 00:20:30,562
-Actions.
-Actions.

462
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:31,897
Encouraging words.

463
00:20:33,065 --> 00:20:34,816
-Number one.
-Actions?

464
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:37,110
ACTIONS WIN TWICE

465
00:20:37,194 --> 00:20:38,403
Actions and…

466
00:20:38,487 --> 00:20:39,905
ACTIONS AND… ACTIONS

467
00:20:39,988 --> 00:20:41,823
Okay. Understood.

468
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:43,700
Anyway, this is really good.

469
00:20:45,827 --> 00:20:46,745
Enjoy.

470
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:49,331
It's nice to see you eat well.

471
00:20:53,752 --> 00:20:55,587
GUKBAP GONG

472
00:20:55,671 --> 00:20:57,589
-You're drunk, aren't you?
-Yes.

473
00:20:57,673 --> 00:21:00,342
Do you have a habit of eating
when you're drunk?

474
00:21:01,426 --> 00:21:02,261
Yes.

475
00:21:03,553 --> 00:21:05,264
<i>He kept eating nonstop.</i>

476
00:21:05,347 --> 00:21:07,349
He kept eating and eating.

477
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:10,269
He'd eat whether it's hot or cold.

478
00:21:10,352 --> 00:21:11,478
He said he was hungry.

479
00:21:11,561 --> 00:21:14,523
He kept eating
but kept saying he was hungry.

480
00:21:15,524 --> 00:21:18,110
I noticed he had a big appetite.

481
00:21:18,193 --> 00:21:23,031
I prefer someone who has a big appetite
than someone who's a picky eater.

482
00:21:28,620 --> 00:21:29,955
CHECKED YOUR EMAIL?
HAD GOOD COFFEE?

483
00:21:30,038 --> 00:21:30,914
Wait.

484
00:21:30,998 --> 00:21:32,582
-Her wallpaper…
-Let's check it out.

485
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:35,377
"Have you slept over seven hours?
Did you drink 2 liters of water?

486
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:37,587
Did you stretch your shoulders,
neck, and hip?"

487
00:21:37,671 --> 00:21:39,423
"Did you drink good coffee?"

488
00:21:39,506 --> 00:21:41,383
-This is something else.
-This is hilarious.

489
00:21:48,015 --> 00:21:49,933
"If both people want to continue…"

490
00:21:50,017 --> 00:21:53,020
IF YOU WANT TO GO TO 2ND ROUND,
SEND YOUR DECISION ALONG WITH THE REASON

491
00:21:57,482 --> 00:21:59,234
JUNG-WOO REPLIES FIRST

492
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:02,863
HE KEEPS MAKING TYPOS

493
00:22:04,781 --> 00:22:08,201
TRYING TO FOCUS

494
00:22:10,912 --> 00:22:13,081
I OPT IN. I'M CURIOUS ABOUT HER

495
00:22:19,129 --> 00:22:23,383
I OPT IN BECAUSE I WANT TO
GET TO KNOW HIM MORE

496
00:22:30,766 --> 00:22:33,602
BOTH PEOPLE OPTED TO GO TO THE 2ND ROUND

497
00:22:34,186 --> 00:22:35,812
You can hold your liquor well.

498
00:22:35,896 --> 00:22:37,272
I'm 95% drunk right now.

499
00:22:37,355 --> 00:22:38,732
-Seriously?
-Yes.

500
00:22:45,781 --> 00:22:48,366
-I'm really curious about this one thing.
-What is it?

501
00:22:48,450 --> 00:22:50,994
When you're in early stages of dating
or in a relationship,

502
00:22:51,078 --> 00:22:53,455
do you tend to communicate often?

503
00:22:53,538 --> 00:22:54,498
No.

504
00:22:54,581 --> 00:22:55,874
When do you contact them?

505
00:22:55,957 --> 00:23:01,254
Occasionally, when I want to
share parts of my daily life, I guess.

506
00:23:03,340 --> 00:23:05,759
How often would you prefer
to meet your boyfriend?

507
00:23:05,842 --> 00:23:07,636
-Honestly?
-Honestly.

508
00:23:07,719 --> 00:23:08,887
Once?

509
00:23:08,970 --> 00:23:11,431
-Once?
-Once or twice at most.

510
00:23:11,515 --> 00:23:12,432
Twice at most?

511
00:23:16,436 --> 00:23:21,650
You see, I value my alone time.

512
00:23:23,944 --> 00:23:26,488
A LITTLE LATER…

513
00:23:26,571 --> 00:23:29,282
THINGS ARE GETTING HARDER FOR THEM

514
00:23:29,366 --> 00:23:32,285
Did you know that when you mix drinks,

515
00:23:32,369 --> 00:23:33,662
you're done for?

516
00:23:34,496 --> 00:23:36,081
Right now,

517
00:23:36,164 --> 00:23:38,041
I am very drunk.

518
00:23:38,125 --> 00:23:39,417
Me too.

519
00:23:40,377 --> 00:23:42,045
I didn't control myself well.

520
00:23:44,714 --> 00:23:46,842
But I really can't tell.

521
00:23:46,925 --> 00:23:48,385
I can't tell with you either.

522
00:23:48,468 --> 00:23:50,220
But it's obvious when I'm drunk.

523
00:23:50,303 --> 00:23:51,138
It isn't.

524
00:23:51,221 --> 00:23:52,472
-You can't tell?
-No.

525
00:23:53,056 --> 00:23:54,975
That means you're drunk.

526
00:23:55,058 --> 00:23:56,643
That's why

527
00:23:57,269 --> 00:23:58,895
I'm not even using my dialect.

528
00:23:58,979 --> 00:23:59,896
Yeah, that's right.

529
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:01,773
-You can tell, right?
-You're using less.

530
00:24:01,857 --> 00:24:02,816
-Right?
-Yeah.

531
00:24:05,610 --> 00:24:08,321
I'm a Seoul native right now.

532
00:24:09,489 --> 00:24:10,907
-You're a Seoul native?
-Yeah.

533
00:24:10,991 --> 00:24:13,869
I'm a total Seoul native right now.

534
00:24:20,167 --> 00:24:23,461
THEY COULDN'T POSSIBLY GO TO THE 2ND ROUND
SO THE BLIND DATE ENDED HERE

535
00:24:24,963 --> 00:24:28,175
EVERYTHING WAS PREPARED FOR THEM

536
00:24:28,258 --> 00:24:31,845
BUT MAYBE NEXT TIME FOR THE 2ND ROUND…

537
00:24:32,429 --> 00:24:33,680
What? For real?

538
00:24:33,763 --> 00:24:35,015
Why?

539
00:24:35,098 --> 00:24:38,143
-You have to go from here!
-You should've gone from here.

540
00:24:38,226 --> 00:24:39,060
Passed out?

541
00:24:39,144 --> 00:24:41,104
They were so drunk
that it got too hard for them.

542
00:24:41,188 --> 00:24:43,732
-We have to mention Anjuilche.
-They should've gone there.

543
00:24:43,815 --> 00:24:45,066
How could you pass out?

544
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:46,526
This is as real as it gets.

545
00:24:46,610 --> 00:24:47,777
How could this be?

546
00:24:47,861 --> 00:24:49,988
THEY'RE SENT HOME

547
00:24:50,071 --> 00:24:51,448
Can I share your umbrella?

548
00:24:51,948 --> 00:24:53,575
How drunk are you?

549
00:24:54,492 --> 00:24:56,578
-100%.
-100%?

550
00:24:57,078 --> 00:24:58,830
I'm completely drunk…

551
00:24:58,914 --> 00:25:00,832
Let's take it slow next time.

552
00:25:04,002 --> 00:25:05,503
YAWN

553
00:25:18,725 --> 00:25:21,519
<i>When someone falls asleep drunk,</i>

554
00:25:21,603 --> 00:25:23,605
<i>they tend to look pretty unglamorous.</i>

555
00:25:23,688 --> 00:25:26,316
<i>But Seung-ah wasn't like that.</i>

556
00:25:27,484 --> 00:25:28,401
<i>She looked pretty.</i>

557
00:25:29,945 --> 00:25:31,780
-Seung-ah.
-Yes?

558
00:25:35,033 --> 00:25:36,117
Don't fall asleep.

559
00:25:37,327 --> 00:25:38,995
-Sorry.
-It's okay.

560
00:25:39,788 --> 00:25:42,249
SHAKING HER LEGS TO STAY AWAKE

561
00:25:42,832 --> 00:25:44,292
Are you filming something?

562
00:25:44,376 --> 00:25:45,460
I think so.

563
00:25:46,628 --> 00:25:47,712
Good for you.

564
00:25:51,383 --> 00:25:55,178
THIS IS HOW
THE FIRST DRUNK BLIND DATE ENDED

565
00:25:55,262 --> 00:25:56,429
Oh, no.

566
00:25:56,513 --> 00:25:57,555
They fell asleep.

567
00:25:57,639 --> 00:26:00,267
But it really looks like
a scene from a rom-com.

568
00:26:00,350 --> 00:26:01,726
I've seen that on a rom-com.

569
00:26:01,810 --> 00:26:04,145
But it isn't going like

570
00:26:04,229 --> 00:26:05,563
-a rom-com.
<i>-Architecture 101.</i>

571
00:26:05,647 --> 00:26:07,732
-Gosh. "The next day."
-The next day.

572
00:26:07,816 --> 00:26:10,110
THE NEXT DAY

573
00:26:10,193 --> 00:26:11,945
THEY HAD A CONVERSATION
IN AN OPEN CHAT ROOM

574
00:26:12,028 --> 00:26:13,989
HI, SEUNG-AH!
DID YOU GET HOME OKAY LAST NIGHT?

575
00:26:14,072 --> 00:26:16,074
YES, I DID
I DIDN'T GET TO SAY BYE PROPERLY

576
00:26:16,157 --> 00:26:17,659
DID YOU GET HOME OKAY?

577
00:26:17,742 --> 00:26:20,078
DID I DRINK TOO FAST?
I'LL SLOW DOWN NEXT TIME

578
00:26:20,161 --> 00:26:22,289
I GOT TO REST, BUT YOU HAD TO GO TO WORK

579
00:26:22,372 --> 00:26:23,957
I WAS TOO HUNGOVER TO GO TO WORK

580
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:25,959
YOU MUST'VE BEEN VERY SICK
ARE YOU OKAY NOW?

581
00:26:26,042 --> 00:26:28,503
YES, I FEEL BETTER SO I'M GOING
TO MY FRIEND'S BIRTHDAY PARTY

582
00:26:29,337 --> 00:26:31,214
DO YOU LIKE WINE, SEUNG-AH?

583
00:26:31,298 --> 00:26:33,466
I LIKE WINE
NICE VIBE THERE

584
00:26:33,550 --> 00:26:35,510
LET'S HAVE WINE NEXT TIME!

585
00:26:35,593 --> 00:26:37,178
THE SECOND DATE

586
00:26:37,262 --> 00:26:41,016
WE ADJUSTED THE ENTRY THRESHOLD
BASED ON THEIR TOLERANCE

587
00:26:41,099 --> 00:26:42,600
It must be 0.04%.

588
00:26:42,684 --> 00:26:44,102
-You cut it to half.
-Yes.

589
00:26:44,185 --> 00:26:45,186
Great.

590
00:26:45,854 --> 00:26:47,397
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

591
00:26:48,315 --> 00:26:50,233
You can drink a bit more.

592
00:26:52,819 --> 00:26:54,863
SHE PASSED THE ENTRY THRESHOLD

593
00:26:54,946 --> 00:26:57,324
ENTER THE BLIND DATE VENUE

594
00:26:57,407 --> 00:26:58,783
LA SCALA

595
00:27:19,804 --> 00:27:22,724
Well, I arrived late on our first date.

596
00:27:22,807 --> 00:27:26,603
I realized being the one who waits
is more nerve-racking.

597
00:27:27,187 --> 00:27:28,855
<i>It made me more nervous.</i>

598
00:27:32,359 --> 00:27:34,444
ENTER THE BLIND DATE VENUE

599
00:27:56,007 --> 00:27:56,841
-Hello.
-Hello.

600
00:27:57,550 --> 00:27:58,468
Hello.

601
00:28:05,308 --> 00:28:06,893
When did you get here?

602
00:28:07,644 --> 00:28:10,605
-About 10 to 15 minutes ago?
-10 minutes?

603
00:28:11,189 --> 00:28:12,607
It hasn't been long.

604
00:28:13,191 --> 00:28:14,776
-Have you been doing well?
-Yes.

605
00:28:16,986 --> 00:28:17,904
<i>She's pretty.</i>

606
00:28:17,987 --> 00:28:19,697
<i>Was she this pretty?</i>

607
00:28:20,698 --> 00:28:24,661
<i>Since we met in a more upscale place</i>
<i>and dressed more formally,</i>

608
00:28:24,744 --> 00:28:25,912
<i>I felt butterflies.</i>

609
00:28:26,788 --> 00:28:29,666
Did you drink a bit of alcohol?

610
00:28:29,749 --> 00:28:30,583
Are you drunk?

611
00:28:30,667 --> 00:28:32,585
-Not as drunk as last time.
-Me neither.

612
00:28:32,669 --> 00:28:34,212
-Just enough to feel good.
-Yeah?

613
00:28:36,464 --> 00:28:37,465
Thank you.

614
00:28:39,426 --> 00:28:40,510
It looks tasty.

615
00:28:41,553 --> 00:28:43,346
We can't drink without this.

616
00:28:43,430 --> 00:28:44,723
Which one do you want?

617
00:28:44,806 --> 00:28:45,765
Regular chocolate.

618
00:28:45,849 --> 00:28:47,058
-The regular flavor?
-Yes.

619
00:28:49,728 --> 00:28:50,645
How is it?

620
00:28:52,188 --> 00:28:54,149
It's good. It tastes just like chocolate.

621
00:29:03,408 --> 00:29:04,492
The weather's good.

622
00:29:05,076 --> 00:29:06,703
YOU MAY REVEAL YOUR JOB AND AGE NOW

623
00:29:06,786 --> 00:29:08,913
BUT YOU CAN ONLY DO SO
IF YOU DRINK ARM IN ARM

624
00:29:12,041 --> 00:29:14,043
They can only reveal it
if they drink arm in arm?

625
00:29:14,127 --> 00:29:15,754
-The crew loves these things.
-Right?

626
00:29:15,837 --> 00:29:17,589
Doing things like this.

627
00:29:17,672 --> 00:29:19,924
-Linking arms.
-Holding hands.

628
00:29:21,885 --> 00:29:23,219
How do we do this?

629
00:29:24,220 --> 00:29:25,346
<i>I was caught off guard.</i>

630
00:29:25,430 --> 00:29:28,892
I didn't know what to do.
Honestly, I wanted to hide.

631
00:29:29,392 --> 00:29:32,395
<i>I felt like she'd feel uneasy about it,</i>
<i>so I got up to do it.</i>

632
00:29:32,979 --> 00:29:33,938
Let me…

633
00:29:35,523 --> 00:29:37,233
You can stay in your seat.

634
00:29:43,072 --> 00:29:45,241
<i>That whole situation was embarrassing.</i>

635
00:29:45,325 --> 00:29:47,076
So I just drank it all up.

636
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:49,662
She may have heard it,
but my heart was pounding.

637
00:29:52,749 --> 00:29:54,042
<i>I felt flushed all of a sudden.</i>

638
00:29:55,126 --> 00:29:56,628
It got hot just now.

639
00:29:59,714 --> 00:30:00,632
Age?

640
00:30:01,424 --> 00:30:04,511
I think you're about 31 or 32 years old.

641
00:30:05,094 --> 00:30:06,179
-Around there.
-31 or 32?

642
00:30:08,306 --> 00:30:09,474
I'm 33 years old.

643
00:30:09,557 --> 00:30:10,850
-You're 33?
-Yes.

644
00:30:10,934 --> 00:30:12,519
-Were you born in 1994?
-Yes.

645
00:30:13,019 --> 00:30:14,479
-How old are you?
-You look young.

646
00:30:14,562 --> 00:30:16,523
-I've never heard that before.
-Really?

647
00:30:17,607 --> 00:30:18,483
What about you?

648
00:30:19,067 --> 00:30:20,360
I was born in 1997.

649
00:30:20,985 --> 00:30:21,861
I'm 30 years old.

650
00:30:21,945 --> 00:30:22,862
Oh, you're 30?

651
00:30:26,783 --> 00:30:28,576
-You really look young.
-Really?

652
00:30:28,660 --> 00:30:29,702
-Yes.
-Yay.

653
00:30:32,539 --> 00:30:33,790
Can I guess your job?

654
00:30:35,500 --> 00:30:36,709
I think

655
00:30:37,502 --> 00:30:38,962
you work in the fashion industry.

656
00:30:39,045 --> 00:30:40,547
-Fashion industry?
-Yes.

657
00:30:41,172 --> 00:30:42,298
I think so.

658
00:30:43,633 --> 00:30:46,052
I'm a dental hygienist.

659
00:30:48,263 --> 00:30:52,767
<i>I am a dental hygienist, and I help</i>
<i>patients maintain their oral health.</i>

660
00:30:53,351 --> 00:30:55,603
<i>For the past seven years,</i>
<i>I've been working at a clinic</i>

661
00:30:55,687 --> 00:30:57,355
<i>doing oral hygiene management</i>

662
00:30:57,438 --> 00:30:59,607
<i>and assisting with procedures</i>
<i>like root canals.</i>

663
00:30:59,691 --> 00:31:03,069
<i>I also work in</i>
<i>periodontal and preventive care.</i>

664
00:31:03,444 --> 00:31:06,406
DENTAL HYGIENIST
HA SEUNG-AH

665
00:31:06,990 --> 00:31:08,741
Working at a dental clinic suits you.

666
00:31:08,825 --> 00:31:10,034
-Really?
-Yes.

667
00:31:10,702 --> 00:31:12,662
She works in the medical field,

668
00:31:12,745 --> 00:31:16,708
and it's a job that is hard
but respectable. I like that.

669
00:31:18,543 --> 00:31:20,420
Dental hygienist. That's insane!

670
00:31:20,503 --> 00:31:23,631
-My best friends are dental hygienists.
-Really?

671
00:31:23,715 --> 00:31:25,592
I know a lot about this.

672
00:31:26,092 --> 00:31:29,220
-You need a nationally certified license.
-Really?

673
00:31:29,304 --> 00:31:30,972
You have to pass a licensing exam,

674
00:31:31,055 --> 00:31:32,891
so naturally, he'd find that attractive.

675
00:31:32,974 --> 00:31:34,017
Not everybody can do it.

676
00:31:35,393 --> 00:31:38,062
Mine is a bit different. I'm a pharmacist.

677
00:31:41,065 --> 00:31:42,358
For real?

678
00:31:42,442 --> 00:31:43,693
Jung-woo's a pharmacist?

679
00:31:43,776 --> 00:31:45,528
-Holy moly.
-That's amazing.

680
00:31:45,612 --> 00:31:47,447
Seriously. How could this be?

681
00:31:47,530 --> 00:31:50,325
Unbelievable. I'd just fall in love!

682
00:31:50,408 --> 00:31:52,577
-You fall in love in every episode!
-No!

683
00:31:52,660 --> 00:31:54,537
Who did I fall in love with?

684
00:31:54,621 --> 00:31:56,080
You said Si-hyun was your type.

685
00:31:56,164 --> 00:31:57,999
I said he was my type but not anymore.

686
00:31:58,958 --> 00:32:00,251
They must have a lot in common.

687
00:32:00,335 --> 00:32:02,003
Yeah, they'd have a whole lot in common.

688
00:32:02,086 --> 00:32:03,421
I'm a pharmacist.

689
00:32:03,504 --> 00:32:04,881
-Really?
-Yes.

690
00:32:05,965 --> 00:32:08,927
<i>I'm a pharmacist</i>
<i>who works at a pharmacy in Myeong-dong.</i>

691
00:32:09,010 --> 00:32:11,763
Applying this every day
could be a little too strong.

692
00:32:11,846 --> 00:32:13,806
So every other day would be fine, okay?

693
00:32:13,890 --> 00:32:17,060
<i>K-beauty has become very popular</i>
<i>among foreigners these days,</i>

694
00:32:17,143 --> 00:32:18,728
<i>and many come to us.</i>

695
00:32:18,811 --> 00:32:24,442
<i>My job is to advise them on creams</i>
<i>and supplements you can buy at pharmacies</i>

696
00:32:24,525 --> 00:32:28,029
<i>and helping them choose the options</i>
<i>that best fit their needs.</i>

697
00:32:29,322 --> 00:32:32,533
PHARMACIST
KANG JUNG-WOO

698
00:32:32,617 --> 00:32:33,910
It suits you.

699
00:32:34,994 --> 00:32:36,412
<i>He seemed very cool.</i>

700
00:32:38,081 --> 00:32:40,041
We're in a similar line of work.

701
00:32:40,124 --> 00:32:41,042
I know.

702
00:32:41,125 --> 00:32:43,086
What kind of personality do you like?

703
00:32:43,169 --> 00:32:45,171
I like someone who's funny.

704
00:32:45,254 --> 00:32:46,756
-Someone who's funny?
-Yes.

705
00:32:48,091 --> 00:32:50,093
I'm a lot of fun once I warm up.

706
00:32:52,303 --> 00:32:54,097
Before that, not so much.

707
00:32:55,640 --> 00:32:58,643
When I'm getting to know someone I like,

708
00:32:58,726 --> 00:33:01,771
I feel like I come across as boring.

709
00:33:01,854 --> 00:33:03,356
That's my biggest concern.

710
00:33:03,439 --> 00:33:06,859
<i>She may think that I'm not that funny.</i>

711
00:33:07,568 --> 00:33:09,821
-You haven't dated anyone in five years.
-Right.

712
00:33:09,904 --> 00:33:11,864
It isn't easy to date someone.

713
00:33:11,948 --> 00:33:13,866
-Your coldness…
-I seem cold?

714
00:33:13,950 --> 00:33:15,952
-You're an icy beauty.
-I am?

715
00:33:17,537 --> 00:33:19,122
Like you'd flat-out reject them.

716
00:33:19,205 --> 00:33:20,498
An icy beauty?

717
00:33:21,666 --> 00:33:22,667
I like that.

718
00:33:22,750 --> 00:33:27,005
You see, I want to give off
that cold beauty vibe.

719
00:33:27,088 --> 00:33:28,756
I think I'm playing coy right now.

720
00:33:30,383 --> 00:33:33,886
I want to appear cool to him, I guess?

721
00:33:33,970 --> 00:33:35,805
May I speak informally with you?

722
00:33:35,888 --> 00:33:38,307
Yes, please do.

723
00:33:38,391 --> 00:33:39,976
You will too, right?

724
00:33:40,059 --> 00:33:40,935
In time.

725
00:33:41,019 --> 00:33:42,145
-In time?
-Yes.

726
00:33:42,729 --> 00:33:44,230
Then, I'll be informal when you are.

727
00:33:44,313 --> 00:33:45,940
-Really?
-Yes.

728
00:33:50,319 --> 00:33:53,114
IF YOU WANT TO GO TO THE 2ND ROUND,
SEND YOUR DECISION WITH A REASON

729
00:33:53,197 --> 00:33:55,658
IF BOTH OF YOU WANT TO GO,
YOU'LL HOLD HANDS TO THE NEXT SPOT

730
00:33:59,037 --> 00:34:00,538
<i>When I saw that we had to hold hands,</i>

731
00:34:00,621 --> 00:34:02,665
I thought it might be awkward.

732
00:34:02,749 --> 00:34:05,251
But we didn't get to link arms before,

733
00:34:05,334 --> 00:34:07,295
so I thought I'd give it a go.

734
00:34:08,004 --> 00:34:09,047
<i>But it makes me nervous.</i>

735
00:34:09,881 --> 00:34:12,216
I OPT IN
I WANT TO GET TO KNOW HER MORE

736
00:34:13,593 --> 00:34:16,554
I OPT IN BECAUSE I WANT TO
GET TO KNOW HIM BETTER

737
00:34:17,263 --> 00:34:18,806
<i>As we were talking,</i>

738
00:34:18,890 --> 00:34:22,226
I noticed he had
some of the qualities I like.

739
00:34:22,310 --> 00:34:25,605
He picked up a slice of pizza
and just ate it with his hand.

740
00:34:25,688 --> 00:34:27,565
SHE LIKES A MAN WHO EATS WELL

741
00:34:27,648 --> 00:34:30,860
<i>That made me more attracted to him.</i>

742
00:34:34,405 --> 00:34:36,699
BOTH OF YOU CHOSE TO GO TO THE 2ND ROUND
HAVE A GOOD TIME

743
00:34:36,783 --> 00:34:37,867
Shall we go?

744
00:34:38,367 --> 00:34:40,203
Maybe I'll hold my bag on this side.

745
00:34:51,798 --> 00:34:53,424
How would you like me to hold your hand?

746
00:34:59,388 --> 00:35:00,640
Is this comfortable for you?

747
00:35:00,723 --> 00:35:02,308
-Yes.
-Okay.

748
00:35:06,354 --> 00:35:07,271
Are you okay?

749
00:35:07,772 --> 00:35:09,440
-Is this better?
-Yes.

750
00:35:09,524 --> 00:35:10,608
-This is better?
-Yes.

751
00:35:15,822 --> 00:35:17,990
ACAVE

752
00:35:18,074 --> 00:35:20,493
<i>-It's pretty here, isn't it?</i>
<i>-Yeah, it is.</i>

753
00:35:27,875 --> 00:35:30,211
If you were to take up a sport,
what would it be?

754
00:35:30,294 --> 00:35:32,380
I wanted to learn how to do acrobatics.

755
00:35:32,964 --> 00:35:34,966
-What is that?
-You know, things like tumbling.

756
00:35:35,049 --> 00:35:38,761
Like the choreography
in 2PM's "Heartbeat."

757
00:35:38,845 --> 00:35:41,556
I want to be good at gymnastics.

758
00:35:42,431 --> 00:35:44,809
If someone is good at that,

759
00:35:44,892 --> 00:35:47,937
don't you think it'd be
kind of surprising and cool?

760
00:35:48,020 --> 00:35:49,689
Imagine that I did a back flip.

761
00:35:51,149 --> 00:35:52,567
I guess so.

762
00:35:53,693 --> 00:35:55,027
Do you have a lot of guy friends?

763
00:35:55,736 --> 00:35:57,155
I do have some.

764
00:35:57,238 --> 00:35:59,323
-How many do you have?
-How many?

765
00:35:59,407 --> 00:36:02,952
I have about
four to five friends in Seoul.

766
00:36:05,413 --> 00:36:07,290
-That's too many.
-Four to five is a lot?

767
00:36:07,373 --> 00:36:10,668
If she has four to five in Seoul,
how many does she have in Gimhae?

768
00:36:10,751 --> 00:36:13,171
Interesting.
He brought up an interesting subject.

769
00:36:13,254 --> 00:36:15,381
And there are a few back home.

770
00:36:16,799 --> 00:36:17,758
Four to five guys?

771
00:36:17,842 --> 00:36:19,510
<i>I wasn't that happy about that.</i>

772
00:36:19,594 --> 00:36:23,514
I think something like that
could potentially become a problem.

773
00:36:23,598 --> 00:36:26,976
There's a lot of debate about
whether men and women can be friends.

774
00:36:27,059 --> 00:36:28,060
What's your take on that?

775
00:36:28,144 --> 00:36:31,814
I tend to trust the person
and let them meet their friends.

776
00:36:31,898 --> 00:36:33,608
-Eating together?
-That's okay.

777
00:36:33,691 --> 00:36:35,776
-Drinking together?
-It's okay as long as

778
00:36:35,860 --> 00:36:37,153
they don't lose contact.

779
00:36:37,236 --> 00:36:38,613
I don't like that one.

780
00:36:39,947 --> 00:36:41,282
Why don't you like it?

781
00:36:41,365 --> 00:36:44,952
If my girlfriend goes out drinking,
I get a little on edge,

782
00:36:45,036 --> 00:36:47,038
so I'd rather she didn't
put me through that.

783
00:36:48,289 --> 00:36:52,460
I prefer a peaceful
and drama-free relationship.

784
00:36:52,543 --> 00:36:56,255
-I just trust that he will handle it well.
-I see.

785
00:36:57,882 --> 00:36:59,675
CARDS HAVE BEEN DELIVERED TO THEM

786
00:36:59,759 --> 00:37:00,593
Open it.

787
00:37:00,676 --> 00:37:02,386
THE CARD GAME OF TRUTH BEGINS NOW

788
00:37:02,470 --> 00:37:05,848
AFTER A DRINK, YOU CAN PICK A QUESTION
CARD OR ASK ONE THING YOU'RE CURIOUS ABOUT

789
00:37:05,932 --> 00:37:09,018
<i>Now I can start asking questions</i>
<i>that really matter</i>

790
00:37:09,101 --> 00:37:11,312
<i>and not those that skim the surface.</i>

791
00:37:14,190 --> 00:37:15,358
We have to drink to ask.

792
00:37:16,609 --> 00:37:18,778
Are you going to have a drink now?

793
00:37:18,861 --> 00:37:20,863
-I'm curious about something.
-Oh, yeah?

794
00:37:24,742 --> 00:37:25,576
This one.

795
00:37:25,660 --> 00:37:27,787
"What kind of person
would you like me to be for you?"

796
00:37:27,870 --> 00:37:30,748
I've mostly dated guys
who were trying to establish themselves

797
00:37:30,831 --> 00:37:34,085
and were always chasing
the next challenge.

798
00:37:34,168 --> 00:37:37,338
So I'd like the person I meet next
to be more grounded.

799
00:37:37,421 --> 00:37:38,589
Someone grounded?

800
00:37:39,674 --> 00:37:40,925
That's me.

801
00:37:44,178 --> 00:37:45,429
That definitely was flirting.

802
00:37:45,930 --> 00:37:48,349
I think that I am pretty grounded,

803
00:37:48,432 --> 00:37:50,434
so I really did think that was me.

804
00:37:50,518 --> 00:37:52,436
It was pretty funny.

805
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:54,188
But I was happy that he said that.

806
00:37:54,272 --> 00:37:56,190
I'm going to pick something fun.

807
00:37:57,358 --> 00:37:58,276
Will you be okay?

808
00:38:00,319 --> 00:38:01,404
I pick this one.

809
00:38:01,487 --> 00:38:04,156
IF YOU GAVE ME A SPECIAL NICKNAME,
WHAT WOULD IT BE?

810
00:38:08,077 --> 00:38:10,246
I have to think about this one.

811
00:38:10,955 --> 00:38:12,164
It's hard, isn't it?

812
00:38:12,248 --> 00:38:13,165
That's why I chose it.

813
00:38:17,044 --> 00:38:19,588
If you can't answer,
you have to have another drink.

814
00:38:19,672 --> 00:38:20,756
Was that the rule?

815
00:38:20,840 --> 00:38:22,091
No, I made it up.

816
00:38:23,426 --> 00:38:26,304
It has to have the aspect of icy beauty.

817
00:38:26,887 --> 00:38:28,764
I'll just go with something generic.

818
00:38:29,807 --> 00:38:31,267
Elsa of Gwangjin-gu.

819
00:38:31,350 --> 00:38:32,643
Come on.

820
00:38:32,727 --> 00:38:33,978
That's so cringe.

821
00:38:39,775 --> 00:38:42,153
I haven't gotten such a blunt insult
like that in a while.

822
00:38:43,529 --> 00:38:45,281
<i>It was so unoriginal that it was funny.</i>

823
00:38:45,364 --> 00:38:46,532
Seriously though.

824
00:38:46,615 --> 00:38:49,493
He gave me a nickname that was so dull.

825
00:38:49,577 --> 00:38:52,121
He thought about it for about ten minutes.

826
00:38:52,204 --> 00:38:54,707
The nickname he came up with
after those ten minutes

827
00:38:54,790 --> 00:38:56,459
was Gwangjin-gu Elsa.

828
00:38:57,043 --> 00:39:01,589
It was boring,
but the fact that he tried to be funny

829
00:39:01,672 --> 00:39:04,383
<i>was funny and entertaining.</i>

830
00:39:05,676 --> 00:39:09,847
THE BORING GUY WANTS TO ASK HER QUESTIONS

831
00:39:09,930 --> 00:39:12,266
"Do you believe in love
that's meant to be?"

832
00:39:12,350 --> 00:39:14,685
I've never thought of that.

833
00:39:16,103 --> 00:39:17,855
Do you believe in destiny?

834
00:39:18,439 --> 00:39:19,565
Have a drink first.

835
00:39:23,694 --> 00:39:26,364
I've never thought
about things like love and destiny.

836
00:39:26,447 --> 00:39:28,949
I believe that there is love
that's meant to be.

837
00:39:29,033 --> 00:39:30,201
-Really?
-Yes.

838
00:39:30,284 --> 00:39:31,786
The fact that I met you

839
00:39:31,869 --> 00:39:35,748
at this time and in this place means that

840
00:39:36,624 --> 00:39:37,541
it was meant to be.

841
00:39:42,922 --> 00:39:43,964
Want to do this one?

842
00:39:44,465 --> 00:39:47,343
WHAT PART OF MY LOOKS
DO YOU LIKE THE MOST?

843
00:39:51,472 --> 00:39:52,681
I can tell you right away.

844
00:39:52,765 --> 00:39:53,891
-Really?
-Yes.

845
00:39:53,974 --> 00:39:54,934
Your eyes.

846
00:39:55,017 --> 00:39:56,394
-My eyes?
-Yeah.

847
00:39:56,477 --> 00:39:58,312
Your eyes really sparkle.

848
00:39:58,396 --> 00:40:00,147
-That's my answer.
-Wow, really?

849
00:40:00,731 --> 00:40:02,566
I like the way

850
00:40:03,901 --> 00:40:06,487
your mouth curves when you smile.

851
00:40:07,321 --> 00:40:08,906
HIS MOUTH TWITCHES

852
00:40:08,989 --> 00:40:10,282
Thank you.

853
00:40:10,366 --> 00:40:14,328
It's kind of like a Disney character.

854
00:40:14,912 --> 00:40:15,871
Disney?

855
00:40:16,664 --> 00:40:18,749
The kind of smile
that animated characters have.

856
00:40:18,833 --> 00:40:19,959
Thank you.

857
00:40:20,668 --> 00:40:23,003
I remember this from when we first met.

858
00:40:23,087 --> 00:40:26,215
<i>Jung-woo gave a big smile</i>

859
00:40:26,298 --> 00:40:28,509
<i>and I thought he had a pretty smile.</i>

860
00:40:28,592 --> 00:40:29,510
That's why

861
00:40:30,177 --> 00:40:32,471
I said I liked how his mouth curved
when he smiled.

862
00:40:32,555 --> 00:40:33,639
He liked it.

863
00:40:34,473 --> 00:40:37,143
<i>He was smiling from ear to ear.</i>

864
00:40:39,770 --> 00:40:41,897
"How many more times
would you have to meet me

865
00:40:41,981 --> 00:40:44,525
to feel sure about me?"

866
00:40:49,613 --> 00:40:50,573
That's a tough one.

867
00:40:51,073 --> 00:40:55,327
Have you ever gotten into a relationship
after dating for a short while?

868
00:40:55,911 --> 00:40:57,413
We'll be meeting three times, right?

869
00:40:57,496 --> 00:40:59,039
Do you think that's a short period?

870
00:40:59,123 --> 00:40:59,957
Yes.

871
00:41:01,250 --> 00:41:03,419
I think I dated for
at least a month or two.

872
00:41:03,919 --> 00:41:05,379
The shortest period was three weeks.

873
00:41:07,423 --> 00:41:10,384
You know what I picked up on from this?

874
00:41:10,468 --> 00:41:13,012
-Look at the cards they chose.
-It's different.

875
00:41:13,095 --> 00:41:15,139
Jung-woo wants to talk
about deeper things,

876
00:41:15,222 --> 00:41:16,891
but Seung-ah picked ones about nicknames,

877
00:41:16,974 --> 00:41:19,685
-her looks, and things like that.
-"What do you like about me?"

878
00:41:19,768 --> 00:41:22,229
-They have very different personalities.
-Yeah.

879
00:41:22,313 --> 00:41:24,398
How many times did you meet
during the three weeks?

880
00:41:26,525 --> 00:41:29,695
We met up when we had time.

881
00:41:30,404 --> 00:41:32,323
Do you have to go to the restroom?

882
00:41:33,991 --> 00:41:36,452
I was trying to act like
I was thinking very deeply.

883
00:41:36,535 --> 00:41:37,411
You could tell?

884
00:41:37,495 --> 00:41:38,662
It was super obvious.

885
00:41:41,749 --> 00:41:43,792
I'll go after I have a drink.

886
00:41:43,876 --> 00:41:44,919
You don't have to drink.

887
00:41:45,002 --> 00:41:46,921
SHE WANTS TO STOP HIM FOR SOME REASON

888
00:41:47,004 --> 00:41:48,005
I'll just wet my lips.

889
00:41:48,631 --> 00:41:50,132
COMPROMISING FOR ONE ANOTHER

890
00:41:53,594 --> 00:41:55,179
TWITCH

891
00:41:55,262 --> 00:41:57,515
-Oh, no. That'd be the worst.
-No.

892
00:41:57,598 --> 00:41:59,183
-No.
-No!

893
00:42:03,103 --> 00:42:04,313
Don't drink anymore.

894
00:42:04,396 --> 00:42:05,481
Okay.

895
00:42:06,065 --> 00:42:07,942
You look like you're about to throw up.

896
00:42:08,025 --> 00:42:09,777
HER EYES ARE ON HIS MOUTH
IN CASE HE VOMITS

897
00:42:09,860 --> 00:42:10,903
-Can you tell?
-Yes.

898
00:42:10,986 --> 00:42:13,697
I could tell that he was
trying hard not to throw up.

899
00:42:14,532 --> 00:42:15,699
That was kind of funny.

900
00:42:15,783 --> 00:42:17,201
But he kept denying it.

901
00:42:19,828 --> 00:42:22,289
The way he tried to fight it
was kind of cute.

902
00:42:22,373 --> 00:42:24,917
Honestly, it wouldn't bother me

903
00:42:25,584 --> 00:42:28,921
if he threw up in front of me.

904
00:42:29,004 --> 00:42:30,548
How drunk are you?

905
00:42:30,631 --> 00:42:32,424
-90%?
-Really?

906
00:42:32,508 --> 00:42:34,593
-How drunk are you?
-How come it never shows?

907
00:42:37,763 --> 00:42:41,141
WHAT IS YOUR CURRENT INTEREST LEVEL?
SEND A TEXT TO SHOW HOW YOU FEEL RIGHT NOW

908
00:42:43,394 --> 00:42:48,649
WHAT DRUNKEN TRUTHS
DO THE TWO OF THEM WANT TO SAY?

909
00:42:49,233 --> 00:42:51,569
I FEEL CLOSER TO HER TODAY
I'D LIKE TO GET CLOSER WITH HER

910
00:42:51,652 --> 00:42:53,445
LEVEL OF INTEREST: 90%

911
00:42:53,529 --> 00:42:55,447
<i>It was really nice. We were more at ease.</i>

912
00:42:55,531 --> 00:42:58,659
I was worried that
we wouldn't feel more at ease.

913
00:42:58,742 --> 00:43:02,663
But we became much closer than I expected
thanks to the Game of Truth.

914
00:43:04,915 --> 00:43:06,333
MORE COMFORTABLE THAN THE FIRST DAY

915
00:43:06,417 --> 00:43:09,378
WHENEVER HE MAKES A JOKE, IT ISN'T FUNNY
BUT THAT'S WHAT MAKES IT FUNNY

916
00:43:09,461 --> 00:43:10,379
LEVEL OF INTEREST: 65%

917
00:43:10,462 --> 00:43:12,298
<i>My level of interest definitely went up.</i>

918
00:43:12,381 --> 00:43:16,260
At this rate, my interest will
continue to increase.

919
00:43:16,343 --> 00:43:19,805
Since we've always been drinking
whenever we met,

920
00:43:19,888 --> 00:43:23,684
I don't know if I'm more interested in him
because of the alcohol.

921
00:43:23,767 --> 00:43:27,187
I think I'll know for sure
when we meet up while we're sober.

922
00:43:27,271 --> 00:43:29,690
<i>-Do you think you can go for a walk?</i>
<i>-Yes, I'd like that.</i>

923
00:43:29,773 --> 00:43:31,066
<i>I like going for walks at night.</i>

924
00:43:31,650 --> 00:43:32,901
-It's so pretty.
-Yeah.

925
00:43:32,985 --> 00:43:33,944
THEY EVEN LINK ARMS

926
00:43:34,028 --> 00:43:36,405
-We have to go to work tomorrow.
-I know.

927
00:43:36,488 --> 00:43:38,616
It isn't even tomorrow.
It's in a few hours.

928
00:43:38,699 --> 00:43:40,492
I start at six in the afternoon tomorrow.

929
00:43:41,869 --> 00:43:42,911
Good for you.

930
00:43:44,246 --> 00:43:46,915
-The next date is our last, right?
-Yeah.

931
00:43:46,999 --> 00:43:48,959
It does seem short.

932
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:51,170
I think so too.

933
00:43:51,253 --> 00:43:54,840
We have to make up our minds
the next time we meet.

934
00:43:54,923 --> 00:43:59,303
I did think that it would've been nicer
if we had a bit more time.

935
00:43:59,386 --> 00:44:03,807
Making a decision
after only meeting three times…

936
00:44:03,891 --> 00:44:06,060
Is that strange
for people in their thirties?

937
00:44:06,143 --> 00:44:10,689
I don't know.
I have so much on my mind right now.

938
00:44:10,773 --> 00:44:15,486
I just hope we have a good time
so we aren't left with any regrets.

939
00:44:16,820 --> 00:44:17,696
Take care.

940
00:44:22,618 --> 00:44:25,537
THEIR SECOND DRUNK DATE HAS ENDED

941
00:44:25,621 --> 00:44:27,498
THE NEXT DAY

942
00:44:27,581 --> 00:44:29,416
-DID YOU GET TO WORK OKAY?
-YES

943
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:30,459
NO

944
00:44:30,542 --> 00:44:32,419
HA HA
I'M DYING

945
00:44:32,503 --> 00:44:34,296
I'VE BEEN WONDERING ABOUT SOMETHING
CAN I ASK?

946
00:44:34,380 --> 00:44:35,589
YES, WHAT IS IT?

947
00:44:35,673 --> 00:44:37,841
HOW LONG WAS YOUR LAST RELATIONSHIP?

948
00:44:37,925 --> 00:44:40,636
ABOUT A YEAR AND A HALF
WHY WERE YOU SUDDENLY CURIOUS ABOUT THAT?

949
00:44:40,719 --> 00:44:42,721
I WAS WONDERING IF THAT WAS
ENOUGH TIME TO MOVE ON

950
00:44:42,805 --> 00:44:44,973
FOR ME, 6 MONTHS IS ENOUGH
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

951
00:44:45,057 --> 00:44:46,725
IT'S BEEN TOO LONG FOR ME
I'VE LOST TOUCH

952
00:44:46,809 --> 00:44:48,519
MY FRIENDS SAY
I'M LIKE A FIRST-TIME DATER

953
00:44:48,602 --> 00:44:49,895
AN HONORARY FIRST-TIME DATER

954
00:44:49,978 --> 00:44:52,439
AN HONORARY FIRST-TIME DATER

955
00:44:52,523 --> 00:44:54,441
How dare he call her that?

956
00:44:54,525 --> 00:44:55,651
I refuse to accept it!

957
00:44:55,734 --> 00:44:57,152
Why would he tease her?

958
00:44:57,236 --> 00:44:58,404
It's only been four years.

959
00:44:58,487 --> 00:44:59,738
I HAVE SOMETHING TO TELL YOU

960
00:44:59,822 --> 00:45:01,490
WHAT IS IT?

961
00:45:01,573 --> 00:45:03,242
CAN WE SPEAK INFORMALLY ON OUR LAST DATE?

962
00:45:03,325 --> 00:45:06,078
HA HA
LET'S GIVE IT A SHOT!

963
00:45:06,161 --> 00:45:07,538
WE'RE MEETING VERY EARLY TOMORROW

964
00:45:07,621 --> 00:45:08,956
OH NO, YOU'LL SEE MY PUFFY FACE

965
00:45:09,039 --> 00:45:10,082
HOW PUFFY COULD IT GET?

966
00:45:10,165 --> 00:45:12,543
IT GETS REALLY PUFFY
MY PIGGY SIDE WON AND I ATE A LOT TODAY

967
00:45:12,626 --> 00:45:15,462
YOU HAVE A PIGGY SIDE? I'M THE PIGGY HERE
REMEMBER AT THE GUKBAP PLACE?

968
00:45:15,546 --> 00:45:17,131
HA HA HA

969
00:45:17,214 --> 00:45:18,674
LET'S HAVE FUN TOMORROW!
SLEEP TIGHT

970
00:45:18,757 --> 00:45:21,718
YEAH, SEE YOU LATER!

971
00:45:21,802 --> 00:45:23,971
THE THIRD DATE

972
00:45:29,977 --> 00:45:33,772
TODAY'S DATE IS A SOBER, DAYTIME DATE
ONCE THE SUN GOES DOWN, THE DATE ENDS

973
00:45:34,606 --> 00:45:37,067
<i>When this time is over, it's really over.</i>

974
00:45:37,151 --> 00:45:39,278
<i>That really sank in.</i>

975
00:45:40,320 --> 00:45:41,822
<i>No matter what we decide,</i>

976
00:45:41,905 --> 00:45:43,866
<i>I wanted to keep things easy</i>
<i>and have no regrets.</i>

977
00:45:48,912 --> 00:45:52,499
<i>I was wondering why a car stopped</i>
<i>in front of me and wouldn't move.</i>

978
00:45:52,583 --> 00:45:53,917
Hi, Seung-ah.

979
00:45:54,001 --> 00:45:55,836
-Hello.
-Hello.

980
00:45:57,087 --> 00:45:58,464
Oh, my.

981
00:45:58,547 --> 00:46:00,424
-Here's your coffee.
-Thank you.

982
00:46:00,507 --> 00:46:01,425
It's been a while.

983
00:46:02,676 --> 00:46:04,303
You're a good driver.

984
00:46:05,179 --> 00:46:09,057
<i>My heart skipped a beat</i>
<i>when I noticed he was a good driver.</i>

985
00:46:09,141 --> 00:46:11,351
Why aren't you speaking informally to me?

986
00:46:11,435 --> 00:46:13,061
THEY PROMISED TO SPEAK INFORMALLY TODAY

987
00:46:13,145 --> 00:46:15,439
Then, I'm going back to
speaking formally to you too.

988
00:46:15,522 --> 00:46:16,773
I'll speak informally.

989
00:46:16,857 --> 00:46:17,900
Okay.

990
00:46:18,400 --> 00:46:21,069
I didn't expect you
to show up in your car.

991
00:46:21,570 --> 00:46:23,530
-You didn't know?
-I had no idea.

992
00:46:24,406 --> 00:46:28,327
<i>He really felt like a boyfriend to me</i>
<i>at that moment.</i>

993
00:46:29,912 --> 00:46:32,247
TAROT AND ASTROLOGY CAFE "KKAEBI KING"
SOBER, DAYTIME DATE

994
00:46:32,331 --> 00:46:35,584
Based on his personality
through the fortune reading,

995
00:46:35,667 --> 00:46:38,212
he tends to be a bit small-minded.

996
00:46:38,295 --> 00:46:39,630
JUNG-WOO
1. A BIT PETTY

997
00:46:39,713 --> 00:46:41,423
He isn't very petty though.

998
00:46:41,507 --> 00:46:43,842
He may stay sulky when he gets upset.

999
00:46:43,926 --> 00:46:45,677
"I thought he was over it,

1000
00:46:45,761 --> 00:46:47,971
so why does he keep bringing it up?"
Things like that.

1001
00:46:48,055 --> 00:46:51,558
He doesn't like being
completely left alone…

1002
00:46:51,642 --> 00:46:54,019
-Really?
-…nor does he like too much meddling.

1003
00:46:54,102 --> 00:46:55,229
It's contradicting.

1004
00:46:55,312 --> 00:46:57,064
2. HE NEEDS THE RIGHT AMOUNT OF ATTENTION

1005
00:46:57,147 --> 00:46:59,358
Yes, I think I'm like that.

1006
00:46:59,441 --> 00:47:00,692
She said he gets sulky.

1007
00:47:00,776 --> 00:47:04,112
He gets sulky if you ignore him
and when you give him too much attention.

1008
00:47:04,196 --> 00:47:06,740
I feel totally exposed.

1009
00:47:06,823 --> 00:47:09,159
Ask what you've been wondering about.

1010
00:47:09,243 --> 00:47:12,120
When will I get to date someone?

1011
00:47:12,204 --> 00:47:13,455
Pick five cards from here.

1012
00:47:15,207 --> 00:47:17,084
We aren't off to a good start.

1013
00:47:17,167 --> 00:47:18,001
Really?

1014
00:47:18,710 --> 00:47:21,004
"THE FOOL" CARD CAME OUT

1015
00:47:21,088 --> 00:47:23,048
It wouldn't mean you're wise.

1016
00:47:23,131 --> 00:47:24,091
SEUNG-AH
FOOL

1017
00:47:24,675 --> 00:47:26,718
It could mean that
you don't know much about men

1018
00:47:26,802 --> 00:47:29,346
or you don't know much about dating.

1019
00:47:29,429 --> 00:47:32,224
If you want to date someone,
you have to play hard to get,

1020
00:47:32,307 --> 00:47:34,351
but you aren't capable of that.

1021
00:47:35,352 --> 00:47:39,815
Even if you started dating,
I don't think you'd be good at it.

1022
00:47:39,898 --> 00:47:41,900
<i>Between a clueless bear and a sly fox,</i>

1023
00:47:42,818 --> 00:47:44,778
<i>I think she's a bear.</i>

1024
00:47:45,487 --> 00:47:49,283
I did think that she wasn't
exactly smooth or experienced.

1025
00:47:49,366 --> 00:47:51,702
Firstly, you got "the Fool."

1026
00:47:51,785 --> 00:47:55,205
This man is carrying sticks like this.
Can he see what's ahead of him?

1027
00:47:55,289 --> 00:47:56,790
-He can't see.
-He can't.

1028
00:47:56,873 --> 00:48:01,795
You might think that there weren't
any nice guys around you.

1029
00:48:01,878 --> 00:48:03,922
There aren't any guys around me.

1030
00:48:04,548 --> 00:48:06,258
So I ended up being single.

1031
00:48:06,341 --> 00:48:09,136
My workplace is filled with women too.

1032
00:48:09,219 --> 00:48:11,471
But the environment around me…

1033
00:48:11,555 --> 00:48:13,682
You blame your surroundings a lot,

1034
00:48:13,765 --> 00:48:16,184
but you must lift your head first to see.

1035
00:48:16,268 --> 00:48:17,853
I found it…

1036
00:48:18,729 --> 00:48:19,605
hard to agree.

1037
00:48:19,688 --> 00:48:22,316
Except for a few times,
I didn't have that many opportunities.

1038
00:48:22,399 --> 00:48:24,568
You just make good impressions on others.

1039
00:48:25,485 --> 00:48:27,362
But you remain a fool.

1040
00:48:28,196 --> 00:48:30,407
How sad. What do we do?

1041
00:48:30,490 --> 00:48:31,533
SUMMARY: A POPULAR FOOL

1042
00:48:31,617 --> 00:48:32,701
Camping?

1043
00:48:32,784 --> 00:48:34,036
Have you gone camping before?

1044
00:48:34,119 --> 00:48:36,330
-My friend likes to go camping.
-Really?

1045
00:48:36,413 --> 00:48:37,789
I've gone with him.

1046
00:48:37,873 --> 00:48:40,667
You said you had
about four to five guy friends in Seoul.

1047
00:48:40,751 --> 00:48:43,295
How often do you
contact them and meet them?

1048
00:48:43,879 --> 00:48:46,214
-Her guy friends keep bothering him.
-I know.

1049
00:48:46,298 --> 00:48:49,343
If I have nothing to do or I'm bored

1050
00:48:49,426 --> 00:48:51,887
and if there's someone
who's also bored, we'd meet up.

1051
00:48:51,970 --> 00:48:56,516
Of those four to five guys,
do you think any one of them are into you?

1052
00:48:56,600 --> 00:48:58,018
Of course!

1053
00:48:58,101 --> 00:49:00,646
Seung-ah's the bear type, right?

1054
00:49:00,729 --> 00:49:04,316
She thinks that all that matters is
that she doesn't have feelings for them.

1055
00:49:04,399 --> 00:49:05,567
That's the problem.

1056
00:49:05,651 --> 00:49:07,819
-She just has to handle it well.
-You see…

1057
00:49:08,445 --> 00:49:10,072
No. From the boyfriend's perspective,

1058
00:49:10,155 --> 00:49:11,740
even if his girlfriend isn't interested,

1059
00:49:11,823 --> 00:49:14,451
other guys keep flirting with her
and hope that she'll break up.

1060
00:49:14,534 --> 00:49:15,952
How could he like a guy like that?

1061
00:49:16,036 --> 00:49:19,247
Since Seung-ah hasn't had a boyfriend
for four to five years,

1062
00:49:19,331 --> 00:49:22,042
she kept the guys as friends
because she's lost touch.

1063
00:49:22,125 --> 00:49:25,462
But if she gets a boyfriend,
some of those guys will get jealous.

1064
00:49:25,545 --> 00:49:28,590
Jung-woo said he wanted
a drama-free relationship.

1065
00:49:28,674 --> 00:49:31,301
-He doesn't want any stress.
-He wants to eliminate those things.

1066
00:49:31,385 --> 00:49:35,555
That's why those guy friends are an issue.
Honestly, though, it should bother him.

1067
00:49:35,639 --> 00:49:40,185
Of those four to five guys,
do you think any one of them are into you?

1068
00:49:40,769 --> 00:49:42,688
-Yes or no?
-No.

1069
00:49:42,771 --> 00:49:43,939
-Seriously?
-Yeah.

1070
00:49:44,606 --> 00:49:45,440
You never know.

1071
00:49:45,524 --> 00:49:47,943
If they were interested in me,
we wouldn't be friends.

1072
00:49:48,527 --> 00:49:49,903
You wouldn't know though.

1073
00:49:49,986 --> 00:49:53,281
They would've made it obvious
a long time ago

1074
00:49:53,365 --> 00:49:55,033
if they were interested in me.

1075
00:49:55,575 --> 00:49:57,494
Didn't you see the Tarot card earlier?

1076
00:49:57,577 --> 00:49:59,830
You're just looking down
when they're making it obvious.

1077
00:50:01,748 --> 00:50:04,084
He asked about my guy friends again.

1078
00:50:04,167 --> 00:50:07,629
He must not have
a lot of friends who are women.

1079
00:50:07,713 --> 00:50:09,965
I think that's why it bothers him.

1080
00:50:10,048 --> 00:50:14,052
What Jung-woo said to Seung-ah
is a huge compliment.

1081
00:50:14,136 --> 00:50:15,637
-Yeah.
-You know what that means?

1082
00:50:15,721 --> 00:50:18,515
It means, "How could they not
like someone as pretty as you?"

1083
00:50:18,598 --> 00:50:20,892
"How could they not like you
when I like you?"

1084
00:50:21,476 --> 00:50:22,894
That's what he means. You know why?

1085
00:50:23,895 --> 00:50:24,730
Let's move on.

1086
00:50:24,813 --> 00:50:26,481
Why? I want to know.

1087
00:50:26,565 --> 00:50:29,192
When I tell a guy that I have guy friends,
they believe me.

1088
00:50:29,276 --> 00:50:31,778
No one has ever said
that the friend probably likes me.

1089
00:50:33,572 --> 00:50:35,490
-Come on.
-I'm serious.

1090
00:50:35,574 --> 00:50:36,575
Come on.

1091
00:50:37,075 --> 00:50:37,909
Thank you.

1092
00:50:37,993 --> 00:50:39,327
A QUICK CAFE STOP BEFORE CAMPING

1093
00:50:39,911 --> 00:50:41,788
TAKING PHOTOS BEFORE THEY EAT

1094
00:50:42,664 --> 00:50:44,416
-Is that a good angle?
-Hey, old man.

1095
00:50:44,499 --> 00:50:45,333
What?

1096
00:50:46,918 --> 00:50:49,045
-What's wrong?
-I'm not good at taking photos either.

1097
00:50:49,129 --> 00:50:50,922
Want to see who takes better photos?

1098
00:50:51,006 --> 00:50:53,884
You should stand closer to the flowers.

1099
00:50:53,967 --> 00:50:55,469
I'm really bad at taking photos.

1100
00:50:55,552 --> 00:50:57,929
JUNG-WOO, SHOT BY SEUNG-AH

1101
00:50:58,013 --> 00:50:59,347
I'll take multiple shots.

1102
00:51:00,432 --> 00:51:02,225
Look over here and look at the flowers.

1103
00:51:03,894 --> 00:51:05,604
-I think I won.
-Let me see.

1104
00:51:06,688 --> 00:51:08,315
Come on. What is that?

1105
00:51:08,398 --> 00:51:10,901
-What? It came out well.
-You're really bad at this.

1106
00:51:11,693 --> 00:51:13,153
<i>-It came out well.</i>
<i>-No, it didn't.</i>

1107
00:51:13,236 --> 00:51:15,489
<i>Most importantly,</i>
<i>photos are all about composition.</i>

1108
00:51:15,572 --> 00:51:16,823
<i>The composition is awful.</i>

1109
00:51:17,407 --> 00:51:18,575
What is this?

1110
00:51:18,658 --> 00:51:20,160
I look like a skeleton.

1111
00:51:20,744 --> 00:51:22,078
You failed.

1112
00:51:22,162 --> 00:51:24,831
Man, I'm never going to
ask you to take photos of me.

1113
00:51:25,415 --> 00:51:26,249
Are you good at this?

1114
00:51:27,250 --> 00:51:28,293
Do you have big hands?

1115
00:51:28,376 --> 00:51:30,337
-What do you mean? Thumb wrestling?
-Yeah.

1116
00:51:30,420 --> 00:51:32,130
-Ready, go.
-Ready, go.

1117
00:51:35,884 --> 00:51:36,927
-Hey.
-Wait.

1118
00:51:38,929 --> 00:51:41,264
-You're doing this for real.
-Of course, I am.

1119
00:51:41,348 --> 00:51:42,974
-I'm doing this for real.
-But I was…

1120
00:51:43,058 --> 00:51:43,975
Don't go easy on me.

1121
00:51:44,059 --> 00:51:45,060
Wait a minute.

1122
00:51:45,143 --> 00:51:45,977
HE GOT HER IMMEDIATELY

1123
00:51:47,521 --> 00:51:49,231
That's not fair.

1124
00:51:49,314 --> 00:51:50,232
REMATCH

1125
00:51:50,315 --> 00:51:51,149
Go.

1126
00:51:53,235 --> 00:51:54,194
Game over.

1127
00:51:56,238 --> 00:51:57,239
YOU SEEM MORE UPBEAT TODAY

1128
00:51:57,322 --> 00:51:58,281
Don't mess with me.

1129
00:51:58,365 --> 00:52:00,617
Well, we got out of Seoul

1130
00:52:00,700 --> 00:52:03,286
and went to a quiet place
in the countryside.

1131
00:52:03,370 --> 00:52:05,080
That really made me feel happy.

1132
00:52:05,163 --> 00:52:07,374
-Wasn't going for a drive your dream?
-Yes, it was.

1133
00:52:07,457 --> 00:52:09,000
WHAT IS YOUR ULTIMATE DREAM DATE?

1134
00:52:09,501 --> 00:52:12,087
I think it would be nice
to go for a drive.

1135
00:52:12,170 --> 00:52:14,172
That's why I was in a good mood today.

1136
00:52:14,256 --> 00:52:16,216
I got excited from all the butterflies.

1137
00:52:16,716 --> 00:52:19,886
URBANTAGE GLAMPING
SOBER, DAYTIME DATE

1138
00:52:19,970 --> 00:52:21,805
-Wow, this is cool.
-Yeah.

1139
00:52:21,888 --> 00:52:22,722
Look over here.

1140
00:52:22,806 --> 00:52:24,349
-Is that a table?
-Yeah.

1141
00:52:24,432 --> 00:52:26,560
-Shall we eat straight away?
-Yeah.

1142
00:52:28,103 --> 00:52:29,938
-It looks good. You're grilling a lot.
-Yeah.

1143
00:52:30,480 --> 00:52:31,398
Cheers.

1144
00:52:36,152 --> 00:52:37,779
-Isn't it so nice here?
-Yeah.

1145
00:52:38,822 --> 00:52:41,116
-The weather is so nice.
-Yeah.

1146
00:52:41,199 --> 00:52:43,451
-It puts me in a good mood.
-I know.

1147
00:52:43,952 --> 00:52:48,081
What do you say when people ask you
what your strengths are?

1148
00:52:48,665 --> 00:52:50,458
It's a strength and a weakness.

1149
00:52:50,542 --> 00:52:51,376
What is it?

1150
00:52:52,002 --> 00:52:55,338
When something bad happens,
I don't show it.

1151
00:52:55,922 --> 00:52:59,759
I try not to make others
feel uncomfortable about it.

1152
00:52:59,843 --> 00:53:03,305
But I think this is a strength
as well as a weakness.

1153
00:53:03,388 --> 00:53:06,725
I think it'd be nice if you could
share the things you struggle with.

1154
00:53:08,018 --> 00:53:09,436
Are you good at that?

1155
00:53:09,519 --> 00:53:10,562
I am.

1156
00:53:10,645 --> 00:53:11,479
-You are?
-Yeah.

1157
00:53:11,563 --> 00:53:12,606
-Really?
-Yeah.

1158
00:53:13,690 --> 00:53:17,903
Let's say the other person
feels like something's off with you,

1159
00:53:18,445 --> 00:53:20,405
but you won't tell them what it is.

1160
00:53:20,488 --> 00:53:22,866
Has something like that
ever caused any conflict?

1161
00:53:23,450 --> 00:53:27,037
Except for my last relationship,
I've always had conflicts because of that.

1162
00:53:27,537 --> 00:53:30,206
Why didn't you have that issue
with your last boyfriend?

1163
00:53:30,290 --> 00:53:31,750
I didn't share my concerns at first.

1164
00:53:31,833 --> 00:53:34,002
But he said I could tell him

1165
00:53:34,085 --> 00:53:36,838
when something is going on.

1166
00:53:36,922 --> 00:53:39,257
Once I started opening up, it became easy.

1167
00:53:39,758 --> 00:53:42,928
But I realized that it wasn't good
to open up like that.

1168
00:53:43,011 --> 00:53:44,054
Why?

1169
00:53:44,137 --> 00:53:46,306
I became too dependent on him.

1170
00:53:47,390 --> 00:53:49,684
Is it wrong to lean on your boyfriend?

1171
00:53:50,268 --> 00:53:54,356
I want to be someone
who doesn't depend on anyone.

1172
00:53:55,607 --> 00:53:56,566
Why?

1173
00:53:56,650 --> 00:53:59,235
When I become dependent,
I'm not able to do anything myself.

1174
00:54:02,238 --> 00:54:05,700
-Seung-ah's trying to be very independent.
-Yes, she is.

1175
00:54:05,784 --> 00:54:08,787
But she wasn't born that way.
She's just trying to be that way.

1176
00:54:08,870 --> 00:54:10,455
I'm getting
the eldest daughter vibes here.

1177
00:54:10,538 --> 00:54:12,499
Yeah, you're right. That's so true.

1178
00:54:12,582 --> 00:54:13,416
Self-reliant.

1179
00:54:13,500 --> 00:54:16,086
-We need to toast the marshmallows.
-Let's do that.

1180
00:54:16,670 --> 00:54:17,712
It's so hot.

1181
00:54:18,588 --> 00:54:21,466
If you toast them wrong,
they'll catch on fire.

1182
00:54:21,549 --> 00:54:24,094
-It's kind of hot.
-Yeah.

1183
00:54:24,177 --> 00:54:25,428
It's easier if you sit here.

1184
00:54:25,512 --> 00:54:28,598
What if I splatter marshmallow on you
while I'm doing this?

1185
00:54:28,682 --> 00:54:30,475
-If it splatters on me?
-Yeah. It's so hot.

1186
00:54:30,558 --> 00:54:31,685
Then, I'll eat it.

1187
00:54:33,436 --> 00:54:34,688
I'm tempted to do it.

1188
00:54:37,607 --> 00:54:41,611
-Why won't the color even change?
-I want all the heat to go to you

1189
00:54:41,695 --> 00:54:43,446
and I'll hide back here.

1190
00:54:43,530 --> 00:54:44,406
Okay.

1191
00:54:47,325 --> 00:54:49,327
If yours works, I'm taking it.

1192
00:54:49,411 --> 00:54:50,495
Okay, I've had it before.

1193
00:54:51,955 --> 00:54:53,456
Come on. He's no fun.

1194
00:54:53,540 --> 00:54:55,583
There's no banter. What a dull comeback.

1195
00:54:55,667 --> 00:54:58,003
-He just swallows the conversation.
-I know, right?

1196
00:54:58,086 --> 00:54:59,295
When she said she'll take his,

1197
00:54:59,379 --> 00:55:02,173
he should've said, "No, it's mine."
But he said, "I've had it before."

1198
00:55:02,257 --> 00:55:03,425
Yeah, that's it.

1199
00:55:03,508 --> 00:55:04,926
That's so boring.

1200
00:55:05,510 --> 00:55:06,386
It's raining.

1201
00:55:07,262 --> 00:55:10,223
Shall we put a blanket over our heads?
Hold this.

1202
00:55:19,941 --> 00:55:21,735
-They look so cute!
-Oh, my!

1203
00:55:22,944 --> 00:55:24,029
This is kind of silly.

1204
00:55:27,991 --> 00:55:29,743
-Let me hold it. Mine's ruined.
-Yours is--

1205
00:55:29,826 --> 00:55:32,078
Hey, why isn't mine toasted properly?

1206
00:55:32,162 --> 00:55:33,455
-No.
-Why?

1207
00:55:36,666 --> 00:55:38,835
-Let's not criticize each other.
-Come on.

1208
00:55:38,918 --> 00:55:40,128
I was toasting it just fine.

1209
00:55:40,211 --> 00:55:43,548
I stepped away for a second
and it turned into this.

1210
00:55:43,631 --> 00:55:44,591
Hold this.

1211
00:55:44,674 --> 00:55:47,177
IT WAS ALREADY RUINED WHEN HE GOT IT

1212
00:55:47,260 --> 00:55:48,094
Cheers.

1213
00:55:49,179 --> 00:55:52,515
You know, this kind of looks
like a mushroom from hell.

1214
00:55:53,016 --> 00:55:54,476
Try this one.

1215
00:55:54,559 --> 00:55:57,187
It's just like you took a layer off of it.

1216
00:56:00,982 --> 00:56:01,816
How is it?

1217
00:56:03,568 --> 00:56:04,736
It's gone bad.

1218
00:56:05,320 --> 00:56:06,362
-It went bad?
-Yeah.

1219
00:56:07,739 --> 00:56:10,116
Since it went bad, I'll eat it.

1220
00:56:10,867 --> 00:56:13,286
-You can't have any.
-You're saying it's good, right?

1221
00:56:15,330 --> 00:56:16,372
I'm glad.

1222
00:56:17,499 --> 00:56:18,666
It's really good.

1223
00:56:19,417 --> 00:56:21,503
Seung-ah has her own way
of showing affection.

1224
00:56:21,586 --> 00:56:22,587
Yeah,

1225
00:56:22,670 --> 00:56:25,507
messing with someone and teasing them
is how she shows affection.

1226
00:56:25,590 --> 00:56:27,675
But it isn't working with Jung-woo.

1227
00:56:27,759 --> 00:56:28,843
-It isn't.
-No.

1228
00:56:28,927 --> 00:56:30,887
He's serious

1229
00:56:30,970 --> 00:56:34,516
and he wants to talk about their lives.

1230
00:56:34,599 --> 00:56:35,934
But Seung-ah isn't like that.

1231
00:56:36,434 --> 00:56:38,353
I think Jung-woo felt that barrier.

1232
00:56:38,436 --> 00:56:40,313
Yeah, it feels like he sensed it.

1233
00:56:40,396 --> 00:56:41,523
The vibe is…

1234
00:56:42,482 --> 00:56:45,276
-He's talking less and less.
-The vibe isn't great.

1235
00:56:45,860 --> 00:56:47,153
-The sun's setting soon.
-Yeah.

1236
00:56:47,237 --> 00:56:50,156
-Do you have any last questions for me?
-Anything else?

1237
00:56:50,240 --> 00:56:52,367
Yeah, he keeps asking
if she has any questions.

1238
00:56:52,450 --> 00:56:53,743
What about you?

1239
00:56:53,827 --> 00:56:55,578
-I have one.
-What is it?

1240
00:56:55,662 --> 00:56:59,374
You said you regretted being dependent
in your last relationship, right?

1241
00:56:59,958 --> 00:57:01,000
Yeah.

1242
00:57:01,084 --> 00:57:02,043
Why

1243
00:57:02,961 --> 00:57:03,962
did you regret it?

1244
00:57:04,045 --> 00:57:08,133
Once I became dependent on him,
I kept relying on him.

1245
00:57:08,216 --> 00:57:10,677
I'm not that kind of person,

1246
00:57:10,760 --> 00:57:12,637
but I kept showing my weakness.

1247
00:57:13,596 --> 00:57:15,098
I found myself changing

1248
00:57:16,224 --> 00:57:17,809
and I didn't like that.

1249
00:57:21,020 --> 00:57:23,648
What kind of relationship do you want?

1250
00:57:23,731 --> 00:57:25,024
A dependent relationship?

1251
00:57:26,192 --> 00:57:27,735
Yeah, he says it right there.

1252
00:57:27,819 --> 00:57:30,363
Being able to support one another…

1253
00:57:30,447 --> 00:57:32,240
-Supporting one another?
-…and also,

1254
00:57:32,323 --> 00:57:34,826
being like a couple
or best friends at times.

1255
00:57:34,909 --> 00:57:36,453
Someone who can be that for me.

1256
00:57:40,039 --> 00:57:41,541
Have you made up your mind?

1257
00:57:49,674 --> 00:57:50,508
It's a secret.

1258
00:57:53,511 --> 00:57:56,931
THE SUN HAS SET AND THE DATE ENDED

1259
00:57:58,516 --> 00:58:01,895
ALL THAT'S LEFT IS
THE DECISION THE TWO OF THEM MAKE

1260
00:58:06,441 --> 00:58:08,193
THE LAST DATE ENDED
LEAVE THE OPEN CHAT NOW

1261
00:58:08,276 --> 00:58:09,986
SHARE YOUR HONEST FEELINGS
BEFORE YOU LEAVE

1262
00:58:10,069 --> 00:58:12,614
IF YOU MADE YOUR FINAL DECISION,
GO TO THIS LOCATION

1263
00:58:12,697 --> 00:58:13,865
IF NOT, YOU MAY GO HOME

1264
00:58:13,948 --> 00:58:15,492
THE TWO LEFT THE CHAT ROOM THEY WERE IN

1265
00:58:15,575 --> 00:58:16,576
I left it.

1266
00:58:18,995 --> 00:58:20,413
Did you make up your mind?

1267
00:58:23,416 --> 00:58:26,211
It feels like something is missing.

1268
00:58:26,294 --> 00:58:28,713
They didn't express themselves clearly.

1269
00:58:28,796 --> 00:58:33,176
I think Jung-woo really wants to
get to know her better.

1270
00:58:33,259 --> 00:58:36,888
Seung-ah said she hasn't dated in years
and her friends tease her about it, right?

1271
00:58:36,971 --> 00:58:40,058
But it's not like Jung-woo
took a clear lead either.

1272
00:58:40,141 --> 00:58:41,392
That's true.

1273
00:58:41,476 --> 00:58:44,395
Even when they were choosing
the cards from the Game of Truth,

1274
00:58:44,479 --> 00:58:47,524
-she chose ones that skimmed the surface
-Right.

1275
00:58:47,607 --> 00:58:50,109
-and he chose ones that were to-the-point.
-Yeah.

1276
00:58:50,193 --> 00:58:52,153
Even after the game, it kept going.

1277
00:58:52,237 --> 00:58:55,532
-He was serious and she kept joking.
-Yeah.

1278
00:58:55,615 --> 00:58:57,575
But she should've spoken up too.

1279
00:58:57,659 --> 00:59:00,787
She should've told him that
she teases the person she likes.

1280
00:59:00,870 --> 00:59:02,413
It felt like they weren't compatible.

1281
00:59:02,497 --> 00:59:05,208
-What is going on?
-They really hit it off at first.

1282
00:59:09,546 --> 00:59:13,550
PADO
FINAL DECISION

1283
00:59:26,271 --> 00:59:29,691
<i>I made the final decision</i>
<i>to choose Seung-ah.</i>

1284
00:59:29,774 --> 00:59:32,110
FINAL DECISION
JUNG-WOO CHOSE SEUNG-AH

1285
00:59:33,361 --> 00:59:36,489
<i>Seung-ah is very easygoing and playful.</i>

1286
00:59:36,573 --> 00:59:39,325
<i>I think dating her would be fun,</i>
<i>kind of like being friends.</i>

1287
00:59:42,203 --> 00:59:43,871
<i>I'm at about 99%.</i>

1288
00:59:44,622 --> 00:59:45,456
-Really?
-99%.

1289
00:59:45,540 --> 00:59:46,874
That's on him now.

1290
00:59:46,958 --> 00:59:49,377
Jung-woo didn't really
make that clear to her.

1291
00:59:51,713 --> 00:59:54,215
JUNG-WOO CHOSE SEUNG-AH
IF SEUNG-AH COMES TO THIS PLACE,

1292
00:59:54,299 --> 00:59:56,718
GIVE HER A BIG HUG
IF NOT, YOU MAY LEAVE THIS PLACE

1293
00:59:59,178 --> 01:00:01,306
<i>Honestly, I'm still not sure</i>
<i>what she'll choose.</i>

1294
01:00:02,765 --> 01:00:07,103
<i>I still don't really know</i>
<i>what's on her mind.</i>

1295
01:00:53,483 --> 01:00:54,525
Thanks for coming.

1296
01:01:00,531 --> 01:01:01,866
Did you wait long?

1297
01:01:01,949 --> 01:01:03,534
No, not long. Let's go inside.

1298
01:01:08,206 --> 01:01:10,333
WHY DID YOU CHOOSE JUNG-WOO?

1299
01:01:10,416 --> 01:01:14,754
It was the first time meeting sober today,

1300
01:01:14,837 --> 01:01:20,093
<i>and we had a much better time</i>
<i>than I expected without any alcohol.</i>

1301
01:01:20,760 --> 01:01:23,054
-You're doing this for real.
-Of course, I am.

1302
01:01:23,137 --> 01:01:25,431
Hey, why isn't mine toasted properly?

1303
01:01:25,515 --> 01:01:26,599
-No.
-Why?

1304
01:01:27,850 --> 01:01:30,186
<i>It felt like we were a real couple.</i>

1305
01:01:30,937 --> 01:01:32,689
I had fun.

1306
01:01:32,772 --> 01:01:35,316
I want to get to know him better.

1307
01:01:36,192 --> 01:01:37,527
That's why I chose him.

1308
01:01:38,236 --> 01:01:41,739
FINAL COUPLE
JUNG-WOO AND SEUNG-AH

1309
01:01:41,823 --> 01:01:43,449
I thought you might not come.

1310
01:01:43,533 --> 01:01:44,701
-Really?
-Yeah.

1311
01:01:45,201 --> 01:01:47,912
It would be a shame to end things

1312
01:01:49,080 --> 01:01:50,581
-like this.
-Yeah.

1313
01:01:50,665 --> 01:01:54,043
And I wanted to get to know you better.

1314
01:01:56,421 --> 01:01:58,339
Thank you for coming.

1315
01:01:59,006 --> 01:01:59,882
I'm happy.

1316
01:02:01,134 --> 01:02:02,802
You were a question mark to me.

1317
01:02:02,885 --> 01:02:04,429
-Really? Why?
-Yeah.

1318
01:02:04,512 --> 01:02:06,139
It felt like you were

1319
01:02:06,973 --> 01:02:08,641
a bit too comfortable with me today.

1320
01:02:08,725 --> 01:02:11,310
I kept teasing you on purpose.

1321
01:02:11,394 --> 01:02:13,229
I felt like

1322
01:02:14,021 --> 01:02:16,357
I had to make the first move.

1323
01:02:16,441 --> 01:02:19,402
SENDING YOU THE DRUNKEN TRUTH TEXTS
YOU SENT EACH OTHER ON THE SECOND DAY

1324
01:02:19,485 --> 01:02:21,863
I FEEL CLOSER TO HER TODAY
I'D LIKE TO GET CLOSER WITH HER

1325
01:02:21,946 --> 01:02:23,239
LEVEL OF INTEREST: 90%

1326
01:02:23,322 --> 01:02:25,992
WHENEVER HE MAKES A JOKE, IT ISN'T FUNNY
BUT THAT'S WHAT MAKES IT FUNNY

1327
01:02:26,075 --> 01:02:26,993
LEVEL OF INTEREST: 65%

1328
01:02:31,998 --> 01:02:33,207
GUILTY LAUGH

1329
01:02:33,291 --> 01:02:35,668
"Whenever he makes a joke,
it isn't funny."

1330
01:02:36,794 --> 01:02:38,171
You know, I love stating facts.

1331
01:02:38,254 --> 01:02:39,922
What joke did I make?

1332
01:02:40,006 --> 01:02:43,509
None of your jokes were funny,
to be honest.

1333
01:02:43,593 --> 01:02:45,762
-None of them were funny?
-You're not funny at all.

1334
01:02:46,345 --> 01:02:47,930
But you don't like unfunny guys.

1335
01:02:48,014 --> 01:02:50,141
Well, you aren't funny.

1336
01:02:50,224 --> 01:02:52,101
-You really aren't funny.
-Okay.

1337
01:02:52,185 --> 01:02:53,144
But…

1338
01:02:54,854 --> 01:02:56,981
Well, this is what it is.
You aren't funny,

1339
01:02:57,064 --> 01:02:59,358
but what you do is funny sometimes.

1340
01:02:59,442 --> 01:03:01,611
Sometimes I burst out laughing by myself.

1341
01:03:01,694 --> 01:03:04,447
Your charm is that you aren't funny.

1342
01:03:04,989 --> 01:03:06,115
No, I'm funny.

1343
01:03:06,199 --> 01:03:07,450
-You are?
-I'll show you.

1344
01:03:08,367 --> 01:03:10,119
-Can't wait.
-Give me some time.

1345
01:03:10,203 --> 01:03:11,162
You need time?

1346
01:03:17,460 --> 01:03:18,795
How tall are you again?

1347
01:03:19,420 --> 01:03:20,254
I'm 180 cm tall.

1348
01:03:20,338 --> 01:03:21,547
-You're 180 cm?
-Yes.

1349
01:03:22,173 --> 01:03:23,758
You don't seem much taller than me.

1350
01:03:28,888 --> 01:03:30,348
It's because I have tech neck.

1351
01:03:30,431 --> 01:03:31,599
I have tech neck too.

1352
01:03:32,475 --> 01:03:33,726
No, you don't.

1353
01:03:33,810 --> 01:03:36,103
-I'm practically a turtle.
-Mine is really bad.

1354
01:03:36,979 --> 01:03:38,689
My neck is really bent.

1355
01:03:38,773 --> 01:03:40,274
You have really good posture.

1356
01:03:40,358 --> 01:03:41,859
I do that on purpose.

1357
01:03:42,485 --> 01:03:43,528
-Really?
-Yeah.

1358
01:03:48,866 --> 01:03:50,576
THE NEXT DAY

1359
01:03:50,660 --> 01:03:52,245
GOOD MORNING

1360
01:03:52,328 --> 01:03:53,371
GOOD MORNING

1361
01:03:53,454 --> 01:03:55,081
She texted first.

1362
01:03:55,164 --> 01:03:57,291
Seung-ah sent the text first!

1363
01:03:58,042 --> 01:03:58,918
DID YOU SLEEP WELL?

1364
01:03:59,001 --> 01:04:01,295
GOOD MORNING
DID YOU EAT LUNCH?

1365
01:04:01,379 --> 01:04:02,588
I'M EATING NOW
ALONE

1366
01:04:02,672 --> 01:04:04,549
THAT'S A HEARTY MEAL
FOR SOMEONE EATING ALONE

1367
01:04:04,632 --> 01:04:07,051
-WHAT TIME WORKS FOR YOU ON SUNDAY?
-IT'S HOT DURING THE DAY

1368
01:04:07,134 --> 01:04:08,427
-SO AFTER 4 P.M.?
-HA HA HA OKAY

1369
01:04:08,511 --> 01:04:09,971
THE TWO MADE PLANS TO MEET ON SUNDAY

1370
01:04:10,054 --> 01:04:12,265
AND THE DAY OF THEIR DATE

1371
01:04:21,691 --> 01:04:23,526
AFTER THEIR DATE ON SUNDAY

1372
01:04:23,609 --> 01:04:26,988
<i>How do you feel about him now, Seung-ah?</i>

1373
01:04:27,071 --> 01:04:29,031
<i>After that date,</i>

1374
01:04:29,115 --> 01:04:33,035
<i>I felt that the way we communicated</i>
<i>didn't quite match.</i>

1375
01:04:33,119 --> 01:04:37,373
<i>Even our daily texts felt kind of formal.</i>

1376
01:04:37,456 --> 01:04:39,709
<i>That's why we didn't move forward with it.</i>

1377
01:04:39,792 --> 01:04:42,670
<i>Even when I wanted to tease him,</i>
<i>I didn't know how.</i>

1378
01:04:42,753 --> 01:04:44,130
<i>It felt kind of hard.</i>

1379
01:04:44,213 --> 01:04:47,633
<i>There wasn't anything memorable</i>
<i>when we met either,</i>

1380
01:04:47,717 --> 01:04:52,179
<i>so he is just a good friend,</i>
<i>a good pharmacist friend, to me.</i>

1381
01:04:52,263 --> 01:04:54,140
<i>I think that's about it.</i>

1382
01:04:54,223 --> 01:04:56,893
<i>But he's a tough guy to figure out.</i>

1383
01:04:56,976 --> 01:04:59,061
<i>I don't know why he made that decision.</i>

1384
01:04:59,145 --> 01:05:01,647
<i>Honestly, I don't know why he chose me.</i>

1385
01:05:01,731 --> 01:05:06,444
What went through your mind
when you made the final decision?

1386
01:05:06,527 --> 01:05:09,071
I had a really good time
on our third date.

1387
01:05:09,155 --> 01:05:11,073
That's why I made that final decision.

1388
01:05:11,157 --> 01:05:14,327
The comfortable mood from day three
kind of carried on.

1389
01:05:14,410 --> 01:05:15,828
We became more comfortable,

1390
01:05:16,621 --> 01:05:18,497
but we only had
surface-level conversations.

1391
01:05:18,581 --> 01:05:20,666
We had different interests.

1392
01:05:21,667 --> 01:05:22,835
I guess it can't be helped.

1393
01:05:22,919 --> 01:05:25,713
The fact that she thought
I wasn't funny the whole time.

1394
01:05:25,796 --> 01:05:27,757
That kind of annoyed me.

1395
01:05:28,799 --> 01:05:32,053
I sat there after the final decision
and all I could think of was "not funny."

1396
01:05:32,845 --> 01:05:35,556
When you drink alcohol,

1397
01:05:35,640 --> 01:05:38,976
you tend to view them more favorably.
Of course, Seung-ah is pretty.

1398
01:05:39,060 --> 01:05:40,561
Wait.

1399
01:05:40,645 --> 01:05:46,317
The things that you don't like
or aren't compatible with get blurred,

1400
01:05:46,400 --> 01:05:49,445
and you become hyper focused
on only the good things.

1401
01:05:50,029 --> 01:05:50,988
I realized something

1402
01:05:51,697 --> 01:05:53,950
as I was watching this.

1403
01:05:54,033 --> 01:05:56,077
Alcohol does not help you in romance.

1404
01:05:56,160 --> 01:05:57,578
I don't think it helps either.

1405
01:05:58,079 --> 01:05:59,872
I used to think it helped,

1406
01:06:00,748 --> 01:06:03,960
but seeing these two,
I realize that it doesn't help.

1407
01:06:04,043 --> 01:06:07,296
Even when I was watching them,
I thought they shouldn't work out.

1408
01:06:07,380 --> 01:06:09,757
When Jung-woo speaks,
Seung-ah would kill the conversation.

1409
01:06:09,840 --> 01:06:10,925
And when she teased him,

1410
01:06:11,008 --> 01:06:12,635
-he would kill the joke.
-He killed it.

1411
01:06:12,718 --> 01:06:13,886
There was no back-and-forth.

1412
01:06:13,970 --> 01:06:15,221
-It kept falling through.
-Yeah.

1413
01:06:15,304 --> 01:06:16,597
How could they possibly date?

1414
01:06:16,681 --> 01:06:18,724
They were attracted physically, for sure.

1415
01:06:18,808 --> 01:06:22,186
But dating isn't only about the looks.

1416
01:06:22,269 --> 01:06:24,188
And as Jung-woo said,

1417
01:06:24,271 --> 01:06:28,234
the two are in their thirties
with respectable jobs and grounded lives.

1418
01:06:28,317 --> 01:06:32,446
They didn't want to risk all that
when they knew they weren't compatible.

1419
01:06:32,989 --> 01:06:34,115
In the end, those two…

1420
01:06:34,198 --> 01:06:35,032
Did not work out.

1421
01:06:36,325 --> 01:06:37,618
Because they weren't compatible.

1422
01:06:37,702 --> 01:06:39,370
Dating isn't easy.

1423
01:06:39,453 --> 01:06:40,579
Of course not.

1424
01:06:40,663 --> 01:06:42,832
It seemed easy for Chan-yang.

1425
01:06:42,915 --> 01:06:44,542
For Chan-yang…

1426
01:06:44,625 --> 01:06:47,003
I'm starting to see Chan-yang
in a different light.

1427
01:06:47,086 --> 01:06:49,630
I'm glad to see the results
all the way through though.

1428
01:06:49,714 --> 01:06:52,091
Yeah, it's better to know the results.

1429
01:06:52,174 --> 01:06:53,217
Exactly.

1430
01:06:53,300 --> 01:06:56,178
You see, we all know that
the final decision isn't the end.

1431
01:06:56,262 --> 01:06:58,347
The real final decision happens
after they leave.

1432
01:06:58,431 --> 01:07:00,683
We've showed the viewers
what really happens afterwards.

1433
01:07:01,851 --> 01:07:03,728
<i>The next experiment is</i>

1434
01:07:04,353 --> 01:07:05,688
<i>the King of Hearts game.</i>

1435
01:07:06,731 --> 01:07:09,150
<i>I've always been ambitious</i>
<i>since I was little.</i>

1436
01:07:11,527 --> 01:07:13,070
<i>I had to come in first no matter what.</i>

1437
01:07:13,154 --> 01:07:14,405
<i>I try not to lose.</i>

1438
01:07:14,488 --> 01:07:16,449
<i>I always tried to win.</i>

1439
01:07:16,532 --> 01:07:18,075
<i>A bit of wanting to dominate?</i>

1440
01:07:18,159 --> 01:07:19,994
<i>I'm going to make him mine.</i>

1441
01:07:20,077 --> 01:07:21,495
<i>I won her over in the end.</i>

1442
01:07:21,579 --> 01:07:23,289
<i>Why should I be the one to give her up?</i>

1443
01:07:24,457 --> 01:07:26,667
<i>She's not an object,</i>
<i>but it's better if she's mine.</i>

1444
01:07:28,044 --> 01:07:31,088
<i>The subjects, who are determined</i>
<i>to get what they want,</i>

1445
01:07:31,964 --> 01:07:35,301
<i>must live together</i>
<i>for four days and five nights</i>

1446
01:07:36,010 --> 01:07:39,013
<i>and fight to claim both love and power.</i>

1447
01:07:45,770 --> 01:07:48,481
<i>The King of Hearts game begins now.</i>

1448
01:07:48,564 --> 01:07:51,776
<i>Welcome to the King of Hearts game.</i>

1449
01:07:51,859 --> 01:07:52,818
I'm scared.

1450
01:07:52,902 --> 01:07:53,736
What?

1451
01:07:53,819 --> 01:07:54,737
This is insane.

1452
01:07:54,820 --> 01:07:56,030
Can you become the king?

1453
01:07:56,113 --> 01:07:57,364
<i>I have to get what I want.</i>

1454
01:07:57,448 --> 01:07:58,866
I suddenly want to overturn it.

1455
01:07:58,949 --> 01:08:01,035
<i>Someone may have ulterior motives.</i>

1456
01:08:01,118 --> 01:08:02,286
<i>I shouldn't just sit still.</i>

1457
01:08:02,369 --> 01:08:04,538
-Can you hit the target?
<i>-We have to dethrone them.</i>

1458
01:08:04,622 --> 01:08:06,332
<i>Someone like that shouldn't be king.</i>

1459
01:08:08,959 --> 01:08:10,211
KING OF HEARTS GAME

1460
01:08:10,294 --> 01:08:11,962
<i>Geez. This is so annoying.</i>

1461
01:08:17,468 --> 01:08:19,095
Do you even get what's going on?

1462
01:08:19,178 --> 01:08:20,888
Who cares? I like that there are many.

1463
01:08:21,931 --> 01:08:23,933
Wait, King of Hearts game? What is that?

1464
01:08:24,016 --> 01:08:25,559
Isn't it like taking from one another?

1465
01:08:25,643 --> 01:08:28,479
I think it's kind of like
the drinking game, King's Game.

1466
01:08:28,562 --> 01:08:31,857
In King's Game,
you must do what the king says.

1467
01:08:32,441 --> 01:08:33,943
That's how the game is played.

1468
01:08:34,026 --> 01:08:36,487
Then, another person becomes king
and the game continues.

1469
01:08:36,570 --> 01:08:38,072
Then, in there,

1470
01:08:38,155 --> 01:08:40,449
it's more important to be popular
than having mutual feelings.

1471
01:08:40,533 --> 01:08:41,367
Exactly.

1472
01:08:59,260 --> 01:09:01,887
Let's write them down.
It can get confusing since there are many.

1473
01:09:03,222 --> 01:09:04,306
She's an icy beauty.

1474
01:09:04,390 --> 01:09:05,975
She looks like a chic city girl.

1475
01:09:07,184 --> 01:09:09,353
<i>I wonder what kind of people</i>
<i>will be coming.</i>

1476
01:09:10,187 --> 01:09:12,857
<i>And will I find someone I like in there?</i>

1477
01:09:18,445 --> 01:09:19,655
<i>When I went in</i>…

1478
01:09:22,449 --> 01:09:24,577
<i>I didn't expect to be the first to arrive.</i>

